Dialogue: 1,0:02:03.14,0:02:04.48,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)\c&H1C3C96&\3c&HDEF2DC&} {Warm }Welcome, {\c&H041911&}Matsumoto Sawako! {熱烈歡迎松本佐和子さん}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she really coming on that plane? {volume 2 page 35}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.65,0:02:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Greeting people at the airport is just not my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.94,0:02:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have agreed to this assignment. {no clue what's this anmitsuippai, could be the nameplate she is holding, could be that she's literally taking sawako to eat anmitsu after this; also she says "didn't undertake" without "yokatta" but believing DeepL here; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.45,0:02:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Taihei Finance send you? {shouji could be "commercial affairs" so I think it means some company dealing with finances, tho can't be sure as none of the company names are in manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Matsumoto Sawako.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.00,0:02:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad you decided to start your career at Taihei!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.25,0:02:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving behind many of our male employees, {honestly, no clue what she means, must be "並み居る男子社員を差し置き" but I've no clue what's either ". to sit in a row; to be present (and lined up)" or "to leave as is; to let alone; to disregard"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.09,0:02:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you now qualify as a super-elite, \Na Harvard Business School graduate!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.64,0:02:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never met someone so amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that, you got a Master's degree \Nin Business Administration!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And what an astounding success the launch \Nof Hayate Motor Company's first factory in the US was! {unsure, "advance (into a new market, industry, etc.); expansion (into); launch (into); entering; making inroads (into)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.15,0:02:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stress it enough how much I admire you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.12,0:03:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened, it's not even the rush hour yet. {lit: time to congest/for traffic}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, downtown is always like that these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see... It'll take us a little longer I guess. {guess, last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.25,0:03:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, I'd like to walk the rest of the way. \NLet's get off here.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:20.39,0:03:24.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1.175\bord0.118\b1\fade(0,1300)\fs30\pos(482.318,136.3)\c&HF8F3E3&} Detroit, Michigan{ USA}. October 1980. {volume 1 p.3}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.26,0:03:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, the American automobile industry output {/production volume}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.73,0:03:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced a sharp decline, \Ncompared to last year's 11,480,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.98,0:03:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, Japan ascended \Nto the "world's number one" position.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.82,0:03:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The US now had to be content \Nwith being number two. {to content oneself with; to be resigned to (one's fate); to be contented (satisfied) with (one's lot)}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.41,0:03:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're boycotting the Japs!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.66,0:03:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! We won't tolerate no dumping! {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dumping_(pricing_policy)}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.54,0:03:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.20,0:03:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Impose import restrictions! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.71,0:03:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll take our jobs back by force!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.55,0:03:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Japanese car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.55,0:03:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.30,0:03:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's flatten the Jap's car!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.99,0:04:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.64,0:04:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get it! {yacchimae}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.41,0:04:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out! {abunaizo}
Dialogue: 1,0:04:17.15,0:04:20.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\c&HF2F4F2&}Central Motor Company chairman, Hoffman {/Automobile Association セントラル自動車会長\Nホフマン}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me. Put me through to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.62,0:04:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoffman's play is pretty obvious. {見えすいた演出を}
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.58,0:04:31.83,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(368.763,408.583)}General Manager of the President's Office, Showa Motor Co., Ltd. {昭和自動車社長室長}
Dialogue: 3,0:04:27.58,0:04:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He is scheming to stir a commotion big enough \Nto put pressure on Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.83,0:04:36.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(257.763,415.48)}CEO, Showa Motor Co., Ltd. {/president 昭和自動車社長}
Dialogue: 3,0:04:31.83,0:04:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This pressure is then projected onto our government, \Nwho would eventually cave in to self-restrictions. { that is his plan}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.84,0:04:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping the appearances of restricting exports \Nof our own free will,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.51,0:04:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,would serve to avert \Nany future political and legal repercussions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.31,0:04:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-restrictions and the shortage of Japanese cars \Nwould put a considerable strain on the international market.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The prices will naturally rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, that's what Hoffman is aiming for.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.07,0:04:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If the prices go up, the sales of the Japanese cars go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, Central Motor Company, currently on the skids, \Nwould be able to catch a breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.32,0:05:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's only a stopgap measure, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.41,0:05:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys are too busy\Nplaying their zaitech-like money games. {running about; making every effort (to do); busying oneself (with); being busily engaged (in); good offices; efforts ... money management technique; zaitech}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, their production facilities \Nare neglected and operate ancient tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.42,0:05:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If you compare the number of personnel \Nneeded to produce a single car,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.51,0:05:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the aggressive optimization had allowed us to reduce it \Nto less than one-third of what they need, and it's not over yet. {unsure what to make of to press forward; to forge ahead; to push on here}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.76,0:05:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys are afraid of their own shadows. \NIt's a problem. {honestly no clue who he means any why shouldn't they be scared of trifles so having to revert this, originally he says "are not easily intimidated"; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.22,0:05:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But self-restrictions would entail \Nswitching to local production, right? {actually "on the spot/on scene/local" but this is more clear}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. The workers demand jobs. \NThat wish has to be fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.23,0:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, the unrest is only going \Nto get more out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.23,0:05:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, our rivals at Kostar Motors \Nare ramping up their preparations steadily. {not sure about the exact word, hope they don't bring it up again}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.91,0:05:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayate, who followed suit, \Nalso switched to local production this year. {no clue what's succeeding; following; trailing; next here, could be "our second rivals"? TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If our company doesn't do the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.79,0:05:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, we're facing the same old problem \Nas before, aren't we? {しかしうちは例の問題を抱えているからな but I have no clue what's exemplary problem so copying manga tl here}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.75,0:05:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What I mean is, \Njust like we always did during desperate times,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we should take a plunge and act decisively. {from manga, I take it they didnt understand what he means as well as they had "what I mean is, we're always having to perform a major surgery in mitsutomo company" - といっていつまでもこのままではここらで大手術をするべきです ; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.47,0:06:08.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(394.05,413.6)}Business Headquarters Office {業務本部室}
Dialogue: 4,0:06:04.47,0:06:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The self-restrictions are finally placed.\NThe government couldn't hold out for any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They set the next year's estimate \Nat only 1,680,000 cars produced?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.52,0:06:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was a one-sided battle all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.39,0:06:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll go report it to the department chief. { general manager; director-general}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.90,0:06:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch where you... {not sure what he means by "done/screwed arent you"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.90,0:06:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Department chief! We have just received a telex...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-restrictions, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.53,0:06:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I just received a call \Nfrom the executive director of Hayate Motor Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.28,0:06:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.62,0:06:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto, in Hayate, they greatly appreciate \Nyour mediation in arranging their local production.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no... All I did was provide \Nsome minor on-site assistance. {lit: just helped}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.50,0:06:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your modesty, but for Hayate, \Nyour early forecast of this development,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.22,0:06:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,alongside your advice \Non taking a plunge with local production, {to take the plunge; to decide; to embark on; to venture into; to launch out into}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.93,0:06:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,proved vital, as a testimony to your keen foresight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.55,0:06:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It gave them nothing short of several years of advantage \Nover two other major companies - Showa and Kostar. {/went earlier}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not every day that you see a woman \Nwho graduated from Harvard Business School. {despite being a woman; woman as she is; (in a way that is) unbecoming to a woman; (in a way that is) uncharacteristic of a woman; in an unladylike way}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.94,0:07:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet their fascination with you lies with this factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, what's it to do with her being a woman?! {what did you mean by despite being a woman; woman as she is; (in a way that is) unbecoming to a woman; (in a way that is) uncharacteristic of a woman; in an unladylike way}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.57,0:07:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.95,0:07:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, Showa Motors \Nmade contact again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.20,0:07:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Showa did?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd like to hear a lecture \Nstraight from the horse's mouth, {frank; candid; outspoken; unreserved}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.25,0:07:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,recounting all the difficulties Hayate had \Nwhen opening a local production plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.67,0:07:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means Showa are also \Nearnestly considering switching to local production?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.21,0:07:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Their intentions are unclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.59,0:07:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikawa and Matsumoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.13,0:07:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the evening of Saturday, would you be able \Nto meet with their president's manager?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.97,0:07:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon, but on Saturday, \NI'm tending to some personal matters in Kyoto. {unsure, this private could be anything else}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.72,0:07:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, you! \NGoyo Trading is running a monopoly now. {actually "goyou product" but I've no clue what to make of it, in fact it's just another financial company helping people settle their checks so I'm X2 lost; would assume goyo are their rivals and are a lot more successful ones at that}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our chance to snatch Showa \Nfrom under their noses! {to eat into; to encroach; to make inroads; to penetrate (e.g. a market); to break into (e.g. first place); to erode; to cut into (e.g. time, savings)}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.73,0:07:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In here, I documented all the details \Npertaining to Hayate's production relocation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.65,0:07:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This notebook should suffice to sate their curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:52.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\fs52.875\c&HD0E1DB&\pos(380.487,355.32)}Kyoto
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.24,0:07:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It all played out according to my calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.50,0:08:00.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(371.237,379.137)\c&HC0D1D3&}Soichiro Funaoka, Professor at the Institute of Economic Research, \NUniversity of Kyoto. (Sawako's mentor)
Dialogue: 6,0:07:54.50,0:08:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If the self-restrictions are placed, \Nthe Japanese cars will rise in price by an average of $2,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.50,0:08:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, even if the exports fall, that increase in price \Nwould be enough to cover our losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we might even end up profiting from this. {I hope he means this by "no, even a change(for a purchase) may come"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the American car makers \Nwould also jump on the bandwagon of raising prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.22,0:08:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, it's the ordinary American customers \Nwho would suffer the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's more or less it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.68,0:08:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll become a textbook example \Nof a joint US-Japan cartel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.73,0:08:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But I shouldn't think it'll be a lasting enterprise. {/But I don't see that lasting for long.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.27,0:08:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.77,0:08:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The exchange rates... {hope he means this}
Dialogue: 9,0:08:24.28,0:08:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After 1970, the American foreign trade balance \Nwent into the red.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.28,0:08:33.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz270.6\move(712.25,506.425,712.25,22.325,3007,7469)\c&HE8F4EB&\blur0.47\bord0}Surplus      Deficit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.28,0:08:28.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fscx86\fscy93\move(352.656,64.625,354.275,-21.62,3087,3874)\blur0.47\bord0\c&HE8F4EB&}Japan-USA Foreign Trade Profitability Chart           \h
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.28,0:08:31.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz271.1\fscx99\fscy82\blur0.47\bord0\c&HE8F4EB&\move(666.613,329,665.584,-119.85,3007,6885)} Blue chart - Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.28,0:08:27.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fscx85\fscy106\move(96.612,11.489,89.416,-50.133,3087,3632)\blur0.47\bord0\c&HE8F4EB&}Billions of dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.90,0:08:33.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\an4\fscx95\fscy98\frz270.9\blur0.47\bord0\c&HE8F4EB&\move(442.15,551.463,444.208,238.126,1,2788)}Red chart - USA
Dialogue: 8,0:08:29.03,0:08:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, with every year passing, \Nthe deficit had been deepening. {lit: width was increasing}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.91,0:08:33.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\move(53.188,552.25,53.188,464.125,13,839)\blur0.47\bord0\c&HE8F4EB&}Year
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:33.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs17.625\blur0.47\bord\3c&HA04519&\c&HE8F4EB&\move(366.3,540.817,367.329,467.321,24,640)} (Note) Vertical axis is represented by a logarithmic function \N\N\N\N\N\N\N{\fs14.1} (Source) Nomura Research Institute "Business World Observation May 1984" {(注)縦軸は対数\N(出所)野村総合研究所「財界観測 1984.5」}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the budget deficit \Nhad also been worsening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.12,0:08:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So to fill this void somehow, \Nthey relied on loans from other countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you well know, \Na loan is something you pay back with interest.{added} {lit: you can't go not returning it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.79,0:08:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the American foreign debt \Ncannot be paid back now,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,without printing out dollars, the world's currency, \Nin ridiculous amounts so as to cover the interest rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I.e. we'll see an outflow of dollars. {outflow (of people, capital, etc.); drain (of gold, talent, etc. from a country); leak (e.g. of personal information)}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.85,0:08:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the dollar would depreciate,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.81,0:08:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,entailing a major shift in the exchange rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.31,0:09:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,With yen strengthening against the dollar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct. One dollar, currently traded for about 200 yen, \Nwill then drop to under 170 yen if not less.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the decline might not end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But if that turns out to be the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.86,0:09:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan would be in favor \Nof switching to local production in the US, right? {I don't see how one leads to another but literally, she says "coerced into", although if we switch out coerced to "in favor of" it makes perftct sense so I'll do it}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm getting at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.62,0:09:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the only remaining issue...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.66,0:09:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The surge{/deterioration} of domestic unemployment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.91,0:09:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The subcontractors are probably going \Nto be hit the hardest by that change. {/sustaing the biggest damage}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.47,0:09:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're doing this research for Showa, \Ncould I interest you with these records on subcontractors? {unsure why he says "if you investigate showa" and not "for showa"; also the whole sentence is elusive to me: if you ..., I wonder if there's also any materials/records on ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Reference room manager, Yuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.10,0:09:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I apologize...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.68,0:09:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I never said hello \Nand just helped myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.73,0:09:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I work in Business Headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto Sawako, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.69,0:09:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You've already been introduced to me via a proxy. {lit: from her, I've heard rumors about you}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.07,0:09:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.95,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I always come here when I need a break. {taking a breather; relaxation; vent hole}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the late 70s, I also had to deal with frictions \Naround the foreign trade of color TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.25,0:10:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If we switch to local car production, \Nwe'll be in dire straits, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.42,0:10:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, if that would help, I can get you \Nthe records on the production relocation of color TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.72,0:10:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be my life saver!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.47,0:10:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where was it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.43,0:10:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, what do you think of manager Yuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a thousand times \Nas sharp as our manager Mikawa. {kirete could be man of ability so i'm working from under this, although not sure as I don't see how it can be comparative since she says "zutto"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.98,0:10:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,People say he had a bright future \Nwaiting for him, apparently, {having great hopes for (someone's future); expecting much of; pinning one's hopes on}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.98,0:10:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but at one point he had to take the blame \Nfor some unfortunate happening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.00,0:10:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and was made into a mere by-the-window pen-pusher. {/removed from the line of promotion.} {I absolutely hate this and I don't know how to make this line sensible in english, while keeping "window" in it and keeping CPS under 20 because obviously we see the window now for a reason; madogiwazoku is "useless employees (shunted off by a window to pass their remaining time until retirement)" or in a broader sense: "\NA term used to ridicule a middle-aged or older office worker who has left the career line and has a sloppy job . It is said to have originated from a 1977 Hokkaido Shimbun column in which people who were not given a real job and spent their days reading newspapers at window seats and staring blankly at the outside were called ``madosaki uncle.'' At a time when the lifetime employment system was still deeply rooted in companies, it was considered morally wrong to dismiss an employee who had not made any gross negligence . For this reason, companies did not dismiss or change jobs for middle-aged or older employees hired during the high-growth era, under the pretext of being on standby so that they could work as needed. After the collapse of the bubble economy, companies could not afford to keep window workers, so they actively implemented restructuring to reduce personnel , such as introducing a selective retirement system (early retirement preferential system) for voluntary retirement and paying a higher retirement allowance."; literally "window edge tribe"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Two years have passed since the self-restrictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The appreciation of Japanese cars \Nallowed the American industries to also hike the prices.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.42,0:10:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The performance of the imperiled Central Motor Company \Nbegan to improve.
Dialogue: 3,0:10:51.01,0:10:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, as changes in the American monetary policy \Ncaused yen appreciation,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:58.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(379.25,407.337)\c&HDEEAE5&}Central Motor Company Shareholders' Meeting {セントラル社 株主総会}
Dialogue: 5,0:10:55.18,0:10:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the price of Japanese cars followed suit once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.35,0:11:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...and so, I'm proud to announce that the unjust \Nexchange rates, low wages, long working hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.02,0:11:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,government protectionism, \Nand other foul means of Japanese profiteering
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.86,0:11:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,were met with international criticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.15,0:11:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan was left no choice but to radically alter its ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.61,0:11:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But above all, the dollar-yen exchange rate \Nis approaching a reasonable level,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.12,0:11:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,weakening the competitiveness of Japanese cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.58,0:11:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In time, the conditions will arise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.54,0:11:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,where their manufacturers are left no choice, \Nbut to step forth and switch to local production in the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.50,0:11:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And losing this battle on American soil \Nis out of question!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.63,0:11:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, I expect \Nthat large quantities of our "Central" cars
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will soon comprise a significant part \Nof our exports to Japan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.02,0:11:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not impressed!
Dialogue: 7,0:11:44.48,0:11:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving the factories to the US \Nwould only result in a spike of unemployment!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.48,0:11:50.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\pos(387.887,350.937)\c&HF5F5FC&}Showa Motor Co. Workers Union President \N Katsutoshi Sato {昭和自動車労働組合長\N佐藤勝利}
Dialogue: 7,0:11:48.52,0:11:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For us, simple workers,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all harm and no gain! {百害あって一利なしである!} {page 23 of volume 1 btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.32,0:11:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Be firm in your opposition, \Nfor the sake of our union's survival!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.24,0:11:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let them steal our jobs! {職を奪うな}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:12:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in a thousand years, \Nwe'll be the martyrs to the trade frictions! {fall victim }
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.33,0:12:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, gentlemen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.08,0:12:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the board meeting this morning, a decision was made \Nthat we start producing locally in the US.
Dialogue: 6,0:12:14.63,0:12:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we ask you, \NGoyo and Taihei representatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.63,0:12:16.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.118\blur1.175\pos(383.597,358.305)\c&HD1DFDF&}Goyo Trading{/bussan - actually, they're kinda financial operators like taihei so "manufacturing/product" seems out of place here but we'll see what they're up to in next episodes} Business Headquarters \N General Manager Gondo                   Kunio Tsugawa
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.59,0:12:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to come up with an optimal strategy \Nfor relocating our production facilities. {/how should we arrange ... so it'll go well?}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.35,0:12:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to consider all the possibilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.39,0:12:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. Must be you're trying to make fun of us. {/goyo} {to look down on (someone); to make fun of; to put down; to treat with contempt; to underestimate​}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the fun in competing against a softie girl \Nfresh out of school?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.65,0:12:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsugawa, please watch your language.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.11,0:12:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.82,0:12:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda, we hope you don't go too hard on us this time. {not sure what to make of hitotsu here} {[Formal] To treat someone gently and kindly. In the form of ``Ote Yawarakuni'', it is used as a greeting when starting a game. "Please be gentle with me."\N\N("Digital Daijisen")\N\N"Ote softly" means to reduce the degree of severity, and is mainly used as a greeting before conflicts such as sports.\N\NSince it contains the nuance of "I am weaker than you, please take it easy" , it is also used to admit that the other person is stronger than you, or to show humility. - really fucking struggling to get the meaning across in english, it's really just a general expression of humility}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.86,0:12:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we're the ones hoping for leniency today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.15,0:12:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I ask just one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.78,0:12:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.83,0:12:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem of labor unions, \Nwhat do you intend to do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can trust us to deal with that issue \Nand devote yourself fully to developing the strategy. {/do investigation without minding it}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Goyo's Gondo has a nasty record \Nof repetitively making fun of us. {really not sure - it seems "to lick/taste the bitterness" is independent phrase, but I want to believe it's connected to waht kunio said about matsumoto because it's the same word}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.88,0:12:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, we must do our utmost to get the better of him. {to outwit; to get the better of; to leave (an opponent) dumbfounded; to expose (someone's) nose}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.01,0:13:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Department chief, please trust me to deal with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In anticipation of this kinda scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was already secretly drawing up a strategy \Nfor Hayate's factory relocation!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that would be rather handy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.89,0:13:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll present them with a revolutionary idea \Nof taking over local plants. {hope "in one's own way or style​" here means "something noone else would come up with"; lit: proposal of inheriting}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.90,0:13:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let me draw up a report, \Nyou'll see everything yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. Matsumoto, \Nwhat's your planned approach for this issue?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.32,0:13:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd start with a research \Non the subcontractors' situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Subcontractors?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.91,0:13:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the use of dealing with them \Nat this stage? {I think he means "so late into the affair/when the situation is clear already"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.70,0:13:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've nothing better to do, \NI'd rather you help me executing {\i1}my{\i0} plan instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect to your vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Goyo Division is likely to have already made \Nthe necessary arrangements with potential candidates. {could be "to come to an agreement (in bargaining, etc.); to strike a bargain" or "to take (preventive) measures"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.92,0:13:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we take a non-standard approach now, {/from different angle}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.18,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Showa would be more inclined \Nto favor us in the future. {lit: in a way like we'll have relationship with showa in future}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.39,0:13:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it's the only viable strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, cutting ties with parts subcontractors \Nis one more headache we need to deal with. {/what should ... do}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I want you to also \Ndraw up a report in the nearest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.90,0:13:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.90,0:13:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Use all the money you need. {金に糸目はつけん}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be picky with methods. {/by any means, fair or foul}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.15,0:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just see to it that our cover isn't broken. {could be both literal: "to break; to be smashed a person's back" and something like "backing; support; backer; supporter doesn't to come to light; to become clear; to be identified; to be revealed"; ただバックがワレるのだけは困る - volume 1 page 28; it's "I'm only worried about our cover being broken." in TL so I'm sticking with that too}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.40,0:14:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Make every precaution regarding that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.66,0:14:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a no-brainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.58,0:14:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You and me have quite the history \Nof doing business together, after all. {lit: my connectiong to ... is not a shallow friendship}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.66,0:14:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sato only has the union's backing, but has ambitions to run \Nfor the upper house of the Diet. {佐藤には労組を後ろ盾に参院選に打って出ようという野望もあ}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need to get ahold of one good scandal. \NOr fabricate one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.13,0:14:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, whoa, now it's really heating up, isn't it? {/this time }
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.42,0:14:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.51,0:14:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,After building up our trust with Showa for all that time, \NI'm not giving them up to the likes of Taihei. {/relationship}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.22,0:14:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since the self-restrictions were placed, \Nthe plant had not expanded an inch. {lit: the growth of production stopped}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And our future prospects are also less than bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.40,0:14:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the strengthening yen, right? {/it's hard/diffcult/painful}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.44,0:14:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After everything Showa has done for us, \Nspeaking ill of them is the last thing I'd wanna do...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.40,0:14:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we always end up being the ones to feel the crunch. {lit: ill effects; negative consequences; burden; strain; brunt; loss comes here}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.45,0:14:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Showa is seriously considering \Nswitching to local production in the US as we speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.95,0:14:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:14:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told the Showa's labor union \Nis vehemently opposed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:14:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the one-eighty? {at a moment's notice; readily}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.46,0:15:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's all I know for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Even then, even if they build an assembly line over there, \Nwhat would they put on it without Japan-made parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.43,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's us, the small subcontractors, \Nwho make the Japanese cars so great and affordable! {/thanks to ... said to be superior}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you suppose they'll make us \Nsend the parts there all the way from Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.73,0:15:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That would've been reasonable, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.56,0:15:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The US Senate is about to reinstate a law that says, \Nunless over 50% of the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.24,0:15:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,including parts, is made locally, \Nit's still considered an import.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.24,0:15:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if that happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they suppose will become \Nof small companies like mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be... I'm obviously too old to immigrate now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto, for us subcontractors, \Nthis is a matter of life and death!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.34,0:15:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it within Taihei's power \Nto find us something else to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.97,0:15:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A new work for car parts manufacturers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:15:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking over a poorly managed local company?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.31,0:15:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a gutsy plan, if I do say so myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.35,0:16:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikawa, if we choose your approach, \Nthis job would call for some sharp practice. {/we'll be able to restart the work right away.} {to regain one's strength; to recover one's spirit; to be invigorated; to be encouraged} {was "we'll have a pretty lively business" in TL} {unsure, could very well be "it'll become a brute work/sharp practice"... actually, considering what he says next, let's ball with it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.57,0:16:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Without going that far, \Nwe'll never be able to win Showa over!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.82,0:16:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially if it results in the cheapest plan of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.07,0:16:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That may well be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.45,0:16:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but it also means \Na huge initial investment would be required.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.58,0:16:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If Showa falls short of the investments required, \Nour company could look after them with our own funds. {very unsure what he means, lit: I think our company should take care of any shortfalls in Showa's financial resources.; I suspect "our company would bail them out/loan them" which makes just as much sense with the next line as "our company would take over from them"; it was surprisingly neither in TL}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.71,0:16:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, our company could also use it \Nto do business there. {lit: That's where we can do business with people. - no clue what financial coucilors would do with a factory or what business with people they're planning to do there, if prev line meant "we'll loan them" then this would be "how we do deals with people" but again, why people, like single humans? I'm suspecting "would profit from this too (interest etc)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.05,0:16:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You've thought of everything, haven't you? {shrewd; astute; cunning; alert​ - here it means someone who doesn't forget anything}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, fly to the US immediately \Nand secure that property for us. {TLC, no idea what's this atatte/watatte, not in manga either}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.97,0:16:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto, you got something for me too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I was curious: \Nonce Showa relocates its production to the US,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,how would it supply the car parts there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.52,0:16:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, my research was focused \Non how subcontractors would weather that storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what were your conclusions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.11,0:16:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A few years ago, \Nwe had similar trade frictions over color TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.61,0:16:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,During those, the Japanese manufacturers \Nwere also switching to local production all as one. {to take the plunge; to decide; to embark on; to venture into; to launch out into / all; all together; unanimously​}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.62,0:16:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the export of color TVs to the US \Nis now virtually nonexistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.62,0:17:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Electrical appliance manufacturers \Nmoved everything abroad, including their parts divisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the subcontractors that were left behind \Nstill made it through with little trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.13,0:17:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But that was because the lines \Nthat were previously making TVs for the US
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,could be effortlessly converted to VTR production lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.89,0:17:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In the form of VTRs, \Na terrific pinch hitter had entered the field. {considering TL note here to explain the pinch hitter comes out at a time of crisis to replace the injured player}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.39,0:17:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that no such pinch hitter \Ncan appear in the automobile industry?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.36,0:17:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Cars use considerably more parts than TVs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.11,0:17:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The subcontractors also vary in size. And obviously enough, \Nthey can't all follow the parent company abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.49,0:17:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You were proactively urging Hayate \Nto commit to the local production.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet for Showa, you're skeptical about it... {denial; negation; repudiation; disavowal​}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,By then, Hayate had much fewer subcontractors, \Nso they didn't run into a lot of trouble moving them. {arranged; taken care of; settled; completed; finished - sounds weird if we don't specify how they settled it - did they find new ones locally? did they move old ones with them?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.88,0:17:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.59,0:17:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, have you any solution \Nfor cutting this Gordian Knot? {lit: answer the plan to overcome an obstacle or break out of a deadlock; breakthrough solution}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Together with Yukie \Nand the reference room manager Yuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.68,0:17:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we can draw up a new business plan, \Nthat'd facilitate a closer cooperation with the subcontractors. {I have no idea what she means, lit is "plan that can be subcontracted" but I don't see for the life of it how it can solve the issue of moving them to us??? later on the meeting they also just say "a proposal on dealing with ..." and it's eventually rejected anyway so doesn't matter I guess...; not in manga either}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Please do that as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.14,0:18:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A takeover of a local enterprise? I see. \NSounds very much like our Manager Mikawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.79,0:18:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But hey, stealthily buying out someone else's company... \NIsn't it a bit too overbearing? {overbearing; coercive; pushy; forcible; high-handed}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when you have no idea \Nhow people working there would feel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.30,0:18:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Chairman Sato!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.30,0:18:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,After opposing it so vehemently, \Nhow come you suddenly changed your stance?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we explain this to the union members, \Nwho've always believed in the management's position?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought I explained this point to you \Nmultiple times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even a trade union can exist in isolation \Nfrom the international economic environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.57,0:18:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What the... Don't tell me \Nyou've made a shadow deal with the company! {no clue what's "bid rigging; collusion (on contract bidding); (illegal) price-fixing agreement/consultation" here; was "you talked to ..." in TL}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.70,0:18:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How rude! One should know \Nwhat he can say and what he can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.75,0:19:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you'd be quite amused to see what's inside here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.58,0:19:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.17,0:19:11.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(150,0)} Showa Motor Union chairman: {The }spicy {and colorful }story{ of money, lust and abuse of authority}! {too lazy to ocr tbh, believing 2020 me}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.30,0:19:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a sham! {fabrication; made-up story; sham; hoax; put-up job; frame-up; trumped-up charge}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.34,0:19:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad I couldn't care less whether or not it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.18,0:19:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I bet a great many people would like  \Nto see this jolly kind of article in the evening news. {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.10,0:19:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it's a scandal, concerning a big shot labor union chairman, aiming to run for the upper house of the Diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.16,0:19:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that not an attention grabber? {unsure what he means: It's a great bait, don't you think?; bait; lure; enticement}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.44,0:19:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect to Taihei's efforts, \Nit has been decided that the production lines expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,would be conducted according to the plan \Nproposed by the Goyo side this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.33,0:19:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying our plan was in some way deficient?{/flawed}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.45,0:19:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it wasn't exactly deficient. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"Just" what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.21,0:19:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Both proposals involved a takeover of a local enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.96,0:19:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They were similar to the point where both \Nchose North Carolina as a destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.72,0:19:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Goyo chose a takeover, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:19:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The key difference was in the cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.72,0:20:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,On the Goyo side, it was an agricultural equipment \Nmanufacturer about to go bankrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.81,0:20:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.81,0:20:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Japanese company \Nthat bought up this manufacturer's shares was Goyo?! {buying up of goods; cornering (market) / stock; share}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.73,0:20:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it in the nick of time. {very small difference (esp. in time); tiny interval}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.23,0:20:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, regarding the alternative proposal...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.78,0:20:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Subcontractors Strategy, \Ndeveloped by Taihei's Matsumoto {again, just "matter/case/instance of sub..." but no details about what it actuall is}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.74,0:20:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,was also deemed highly novel by our company's board.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.99,0:20:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we hope for a productive future cooperation \Nwith Taihei and their out-of-the-box analysis. {forward-looking; positive; constructive​ study/investigation}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.25,0:20:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say it's so out-of-the-box, \Nyou should start acting upon it ASAP. {TLC, no clue what she means: without saying "forward-looking; positive; constructive​", please do immediately}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.25,0:20:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto, having helped myself to reading your report, \NI'd like to subscribe to every word he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.00,0:20:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Showa is usually rather slow on the uptake, {slowly; inefficiently; tardily; dawdling​}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.17,0:20:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'd rather have you working for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.97,0:20:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Gondo! We'd be in trouble if that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was just a "what if" soliloquy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.56,0:20:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a bit hard to tell... {TLC, no clue what he means, maybe "I was confused"}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:47.10,0:20:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear the company's new owners are Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.77,0:20:51.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0.235\blur1.175\fs35.25\pos(373.561,359.374)\c&HE2F2F7&\3c&HCEDDE8&}North Carolina, USA
Dialogue: 8,0:20:49.56,0:20:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to turn this into an assembly plant \Nfor Japanese cars. And they're going to keep us on. {/employ/hire}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.76,0:20:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd salute this new owner even if he's a monkey, \Nas long as I don't get laid off. {welcome; reception}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.61,0:21:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've heard that workers in Japan \Nare treated like slaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.53,0:21:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't we all corporate slaves? {/company's}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.53,0:21:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if worse comes to worst, \Nwe can appeal to the union. They'll do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.21,0:21:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time we rely on them, \Nwe end up paying even more! {/asking them is always expensive}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.54,0:21:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we should let the Japanese know \Nthat things won't be all that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.72,0:21:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a shame Sawako and Mikawa got overlooked, \Nbut at least we know our efforts weren't completely in vain. {fruits (of one's labors); gain; result; returns} {/department chief and manager}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.10,0:21:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako, let's throw a big party tonight! {no clue what she means by "let's make grand; magnificent; lavish; large scale; prosperous; thriving; lively"} {page 59 of volume 1}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, nothing wrong with throwing a big party,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.14,0:21:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but really, this is a watershed moment \Nboth for us and for the Goyo guys. {critical moment; do-or-die situation; critical juncture - no fucking clue how this is so for any of them}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.94,0:21:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For Goyo too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.44,0:21:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Even after they set the factory up,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.11,0:21:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll only be able to talk about success when the cars \Nthey make are on par with those assembled in Japan. {/no different}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.66,0:21:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, isn't it wonderful, {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.95,0:21:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when people of different backgrounds{/lifestyles}, languages, \Nand skin colors work side by side assembling them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.25,0:21:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, a few years from now, when every single Japanese manufacturer switches to a local production model,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there'll surely come a time when supply exceeds demand \Nand a surplus of cars would form.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:21:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.59,0:22:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a strong feeling \Nit'll be your turn to shine once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.76,0:22:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray that your business style, born from \Nconsideration for others, remains forever unchanged! {lit is "coming/passing thru heart" but I think he means this; also I hate this word but can't come up with anything better}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.23,0:22:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,IMF - The International Monetary Fund
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.86,0:22:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluated the consequences of the restrictions, \Nplaced from 1981 to 1984 on exports from Japan to the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.86,0:22:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A detailed summary of the damage incurred \Nby ordinary American consumers is as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.87,0:22:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Over these four years, the prices of all new \NAmerican-made cars rose by an average of 50%.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.71,0:22:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Had export self-restrictions not been placed, \Nthey place the expected increase in price at just 27%.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.88,0:22:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of this, the combined amount of money \Noverpaid by the consumers was over $17 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.26,0:22:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Converted to yen at the exchange rate of that period, \Nit's about 4 trillion yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.18,0:22:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Which makes it a trillion yen yearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.50,0:23:05.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEDE7E3&\fs30\bord0\blur0.6\1a&H00&\pos(372.13,96.49)}Episode 2 \N {\fs70\blur1} Exchange Game {為替ゲーム} {first assumed this episode is original to anime, but it was actually the first chapter of the third volume of manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:15.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(378,425.93)\bord0\blur1\fs24\c&HEDFEFF&}Chairman of the US Federal Reserve Board (FRB)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.80,0:23:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,FRB chairman...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,People say with this man's every move, \Nthe world's money starts moving too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Fishing so leisurely...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.88,0:23:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The catch today - two large rainbowfishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.05,0:23:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fishing enthusiast went to bed \Nin high spirits a little while ago. {no clue why he suddenly switched to some fisherman, might be meaning chaiman again but why'd call him a fisher then?}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.62,0:23:35.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\pos(381.73,425.4)\c&HE3F5FD&\bord0\blur1\b}Tokyo, August 31, 1985 {東京 1985年8月31日}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.44,0:23:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. No abnormalities for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.15,0:23:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. The overall situation \Nis still rather complicated though. {difficult; complex; tricky; delicate (situation, position, etc.); close (e.g. decision)}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.64,0:23:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take your eyes off him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.90,0:23:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, goodnight for now, Birdwatcher. {no clue if that's a position or a name or what's the underlying reference here, but at any rate birdwatcher is that bearded shaded guy spying on chairman}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.34,0:23:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Among companies comprising the Taihei Group, \Nas well as small banks and insurance agencies, { to medium sized}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.14,0:23:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there exists a dire demand for the precise advice \Non future developments of the currency market. {actually "kawase" is just a general word for "exchange [rate]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.71,0:24:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, creating a currency market \Nconsulting subdivision is my plan. {actually just "I'm thinking about ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.27,0:24:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask Matsumoto to become the project team chief. \NYou can organize the team entirely to your liking. {entrusting (everything to); leaving (a matter) entirely with}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.34,0:24:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.63,0:24:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Will this really turn out well?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.18,0:24:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Predicting stock prices \Nis a breeze compared to the currency market.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.41,0:24:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a metric ton of factors that you gotta see through.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.13,0:24:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being a math prodigy would get you nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.16,0:24:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, the flair for collecting data{lit is "power of information" but I've no clue} \Nand rich imagination are your only friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.94,0:24:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're yet to find out whether or not \NMatsumoto possesses any of those qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.19,0:24:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm looking forward to seeing what \Na Harvard Business School alumni's got in stock for us. {let's see what you've got; show me what you've got}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.32,0:24:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much, manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,With your encouragement, I'm eager to join the fight. {lit is something like "fight is to well (up); to gush out (of water); to spring out; to surge" but I've heard this expression before}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:47.26,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H151C14&\3c&HD8DECC&}Business Headquarters Conference Room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.98,0:24:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you don't mind me \Ngetting straight to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.89,0:24:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Companies comprising the group, as well as a few individual members were offered a newsletter for internal business use.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.57,0:25:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Alternatively, they were offered \Na customer advice service on a case-by-case basis. {...that is my idea/what I think we should do - no clue what's mei in there} {unsure if customer is applicable to companies}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.08,0:25:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, do you have the data \Non the applications for membership? {/subscription}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.06,0:25:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.92,0:25:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the newsletter subscription \Ncosting 10,000,000 yen annually,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.31,0:25:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the quota of 30 companies had already been filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.01,0:25:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, quite a few businesses expressed a wish \Nto receive case-by-case consulting services.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.67,0:25:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so the demand was {\i1}that{\i0} high? {no clue what's this kane, hardly "money" but could be "interrogative sentence-ending particle expressing doubt"}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.23,0:25:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,With the subscription fee being that considerable, \Nwe have to provide data of corresponding quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.19,0:25:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the slipshod speculations \Ncirculating on the streets won't do. {to be accepted (e.g. of a way of thinking); to work (of an excuse, trick, etc.); to hold true (e.g. of a theory); to apply; to be valid; to pass (for); to do well; to get by}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.69,0:25:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.69,0:25:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to adopt a method for gathering intel \Nthat is profound, covert, and advanced all at the same time? {lit: information collecting has to be done deep, quiet and preceding; coming before; being ahead (e.g. of the times); occurring first; happening prior}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.35,0:25:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.43,0:25:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For intel, particularly that concerning the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.41,0:25:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the less people have access to it, \Nthe more it gains in added value.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.92,0:25:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's something everybody knows, \Nyou can't really call it "intel," can you? {that's why I chose this word, "intel"}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.02,0:25:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.41,0:25:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't we divide the areas of responsibility? {lit: let's decide who's in charge of what}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.95,0:26:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'd like Manager Mikawa to look into the line \NMinistry of Finance and Bank of Japan are toeing. {no clue what she means, just says "authorities; relevant authorities; authorities concerned line" - assumed "agenda/line of behavior" but could be anything, could not even be line and "tokyo kurai" instead; could even be she means "bug on the phone line"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.96,0:26:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda will work directly with our clients, \Nparticularly - specialized currency trading institutions. {I hope she means this by "cover"} {actually "banks" but that's kinda contradicts the function of bank; also unsure what to make of "speciality; specialty; subject of study; expert; area of expertise"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.16,0:26:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.21,0:26:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Date will connect to the operational network of our dealing room, so as to directly monitor the currency market. {lit is "pull the line/draw a circuit" so I think she means literally getting a direct phone connection}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.72,0:26:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As for myself, with Yukie as my personal assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.47,0:26:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be in charge of monitoring \Nthe Market Circles of the foreign markets, {VERY unsure about this suji thing, presumably 市場筋 - found it used as "primary demand sources" but that won't make much sense here and after; likely "source (of information, etc.); circle; channel/well-informed person (in a transaction)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.78,0:26:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,from FRB and the American Ministry of Finance, \Nto New York, London, Zürich, and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.48,0:26:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ministry of Finance and Bank of Japan? \NQuite the challenging assignment. {/formidable enemy}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.59,0:26:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's particularly important that you keep a close eye \Non the Ministry of Finance secretary's every move. {lit is "finance official" but I've no clue what it means}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.24,0:26:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.74,0:26:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because he is closely acquainted to the FRB chairman,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.75,0:26:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and a strong mutual admiration \Nexists between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.50,0:26:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If they come up with something, \Nthey'll start deviating from this line. {again, could as well be literal phone line}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.12,0:26:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but what is FRB?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.51,0:26:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.51,0:26:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.26,0:26:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you get into the Business Headquarters \Nwithout knowing even that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.16,0:27:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.16,0:27:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,FRB is an abbreviation, standing for "Federal Reserve Board" \Nof the US, also commonly known as just "the Fed."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.27,0:27:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It acts as the highest financial regulatory organ in the US, \Ndeciding on the monetary policies and supervising banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.24,0:27:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's the same as Bank of Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.12,0:27:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way, I guess. But its influence on the world \Nstands in no comparison to that of Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.16,0:27:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at the first picture in the file.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.63,0:27:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Mr. Chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.52,0:27:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,People say with this man's every move, \Nthe world's money starts moving too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.51,0:27:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.76,0:27:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure is one daunting task \NSawako is facing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.45,0:27:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess that's what makes her so amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.38,0:27:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the currency market really that complicated? {could as well be "important"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.84,0:27:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.02,0:27:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The foreign trade turnover is $3 trillion a year. {not really sure what ot make of "fee; charge; rate"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.33,0:27:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But the currency exchange turnover in this term alone \Namounts to $40 trillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.61,0:27:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,$40 trillion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.36,0:27:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike in previous days,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.05,0:28:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when the exchange rate was determined mainly \Nby the current balance of foreign trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.37,0:28:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,nowadays, even if the market is still somewhat tied \Nto crude oil price fluctuations,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.12,0:28:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,there are also interest rates, price index, GNP, \Nand even policy interventions that may all affect the market,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.10,0:28:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,rendering it extremely unpredictable\Neven for savvy currency dealers.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.63,0:28:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's all about being an expert? \NSeems like I won't be of much help at all... {specialist; expert; professional; authority; pundit}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.14,0:28:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not used to seeing you lament your shortcomings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.89,0:28:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.68,0:28:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an acquaintance of mine \Nworking in the dealing room of the Taihei Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.33,0:28:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a tour later? {inspection; study by observation; field trip; tour; review}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.65,0:28:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The forefront view of currency market operation\Ncould provide you with that much-needed insight. {to serve as a reference; to provide useful information; to be helpful; to be informative; to be instructive}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.15,0:28:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.38,0:28:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you also let me keep you company.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.66,0:28:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.87,0:28:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how did I know you'd try to escape to here?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.50,0:28:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.16,0:28:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuki, about that talk just now. I also want to know \Nthe exchange bank's perspective on the matter. {/information/data from ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.69,0:28:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You must let me join you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.67,0:28:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.17,0:29:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the consulting fees \Ngo up to 10,000,000 yen a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.17,0:29:02.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H6B6437&\3c&HDBD7BB&\blur1\bord0.1\frz21.3\frx26\fry320\pos(376.4,73.03)}Aoba \NMutual \NBank {青葉相互銀行}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.18,0:29:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we take every precaution\Nto ensure profit for our clients. {very unsure but hope he means "we can't afford inflicting any losses [on our clients with our consulting]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.96,0:29:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the conclusions you draw from our intel \Nand the actions you undertake
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.19,0:29:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,are entirely up to your own investment strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.20,0:29:13.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(370,431.26)\c&HFFFFF2&\bord1\blur1}Aoba Mutual Bank Executive Director {青葉相互銀行 専務}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.91,0:29:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That might hold true,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.19,0:29:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but a rural bank such as ours \Nhas no surplus in savvy bond dealers. {no clue why he suddenly talks about bonds and what's the connection to the exchange stock, maybe this saiken is not "bond; debenture​" at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.23,0:29:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we see another bank \Nbuying up American government bonds, so do we.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.20,0:29:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, we've been able to do business \Nwith relatively good profits up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.21,0:29:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There exists a 5% interest rate differential \Nbetween Japan and the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.04,0:29:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you take the money from Japanese depositors \Nand invest it in the US,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.60,0:29:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you can make a decent profit with just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.44,0:29:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if value of the dollar suddenly nosedives,\Nso does the evaluation of the actual yens we have on hand, {tlc ; VERY unsure about the whole sent. tbh and no clue what's this "taiken" ((practical) experience; personal experience; hands-on experience; first-hand experience); would assume "actual"}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.95,0:29:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,negating all the previous profits if not worse. {/blowing away}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.83,0:29:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, you don't suppose \Nwe could overlook that risk?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.41,0:29:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I believe such a turn of events \Nto be quite possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.57,0:30:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, nobody can tell you for sure\Nwhen the {dollar }appreciation correction will kick in, {correction; revision; redressing; rectifying}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.30,0:30:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what would be the extent of compensation, \Nor for how long it will keep falling. {making up (a deficit, loss, etc.); covering; compensation; supplementation; replenishment​}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.80,0:30:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't talk so callously. \NI mean it when I say we're all counting on you, Ueda.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.86,0:30:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.04,0:30:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,One yours! {guess. also unsure what to make of "本" in english, could be "part/piece/bit"? should probs investigate into a real stock exchange but too lazy}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.43,0:30:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Two mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.64,0:30:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it, one yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.98,0:30:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, one yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.75,0:30:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Two mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.98,0:30:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger. {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.81,0:30:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, one mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.05,0:30:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Those "One" and "Two" they're shouting are units of dollars. \N"One" means $1,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.88,0:30:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mine" means buying, "Yours" means selling.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.40,0:30:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... What an amazing place! \NIt's like we're on a battlefield!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.87,0:30:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This place is relatively peaceful now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.16,0:30:35.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs20\pos(380.57,432.57)}Chief of Taihei Bank Currency Market
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.91,0:30:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,As we get closer to 3:30, \Nbuying and selling becomes more and more active.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.65,0:30:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before the closing time? {unsure it's "the point just before ...; the point of (doing); the verge (of); the eve (of)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.38,0:30:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.19,0:30:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to position regulation, the banks are limited \Nin the number of positions they can retain overnight. {unsure where "sonohi" goes here}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.56,0:30:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To adjust to that regulation, \Nthe banks start selling and buying assets more actively.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.80,0:30:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Position?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.01,0:30:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The banks cannot just sell dollars indefinitely, \Nneither can they buy them indefinitely. {honestly no clue what he means to say; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.27,0:31:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The general principle is, you buy back the dollars \Nthat you sold, and you sell back dollars that you bought, {/return by ...} {doesn't make no sense by that's what he says}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.58,0:31:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,arriving to a square. In other words, the change \Nin the number of positions has to be plus-minus zero. {added because he just says "you have t odo +-0"}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.36,0:31:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However, making it a complete zero is often impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.47,0:31:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore, you're allowed to carry over to the next day \Na limited amount of trading assets. {work, items, etc. carried over from earlier/overnight} {unsure what's mama to do here after katta/utta} {actually "set/fixed/prescribed limit"/"items that you selle and buy"}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.54,0:31:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And what exactly is that amount?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.44,0:31:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, it's fixed at $100,000,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.86,0:31:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The combined turnover of transactions made here\Nusually amounts to $1 billion daily. {no clue what's this zara, could be "common practice"} {also unsure what's "in fact/in reality" to do here}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.54,0:31:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So the sum you're allowed to keep overnight \Nis only a small part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.10,0:31:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, because of the time difference, \Nsomewhere in the world, the market always remains open.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.15,0:31:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So Tokyo's position can be succeeded by London. {hope it's "to make up for (a loss, shortage, etc.); to make amends; to compensate for"}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.61,0:31:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Conversely, it allows for New York and Tokyo markets \Nto be in coordination, right? {no clue what he means by "New York's Tokyo adjustment; regulation; coordination; reconciliation; tuning; fixing; tailoring is possible"; I suspect he again says "new york closes at the same time as tokyo opens"}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.86,0:31:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.57,0:31:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what a 24-hour market system is all about. {no clue what's last word}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.15,0:31:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We, currency dealers, don't have the luxury \Nof being able to relax our nerves even at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.15,0:32:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone working here \Nneeds a recreational vacation once every 3 years. {very lib, lit is "in about 3 years, the body will become (physically or mentally) worn-out; exhausted"}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.46,0:32:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't right... {guess, no clue what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.95,0:32:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, Nakayama, when do you think the dollar appreciation correction will take place and in what form?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.70,0:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A leading question won't work on me. {to trick someone (into confirming or revealing the truth); to ask a leading question​} {idk how's that a leading, it's pretty direct}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.72,0:32:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know the news. \NYou opened a currency market consulting department.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.21,0:32:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be the one asking that question. {/I was the one wanting to ask that}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.97,0:32:29.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord0\blur1\fs30\c&HE8FFFE&\pos(387.59,403.54)}September 16th, 1985 \N4:50 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.30,0:32:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to the strong dollar policy we've been upholding, {and the dollar appreciation}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.03,0:32:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the US-manufactured goods \Nbecome less and less competitive. {on the international market}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.26,0:32:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It also hits our agricultural exports hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.81,0:32:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, unemployed men are flooding the streets. {unsure why he only limits it to city, most likely means streets [of the us]}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.02,0:32:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Both from Japan and from Europe, \Nwe hear one voice after another, {no clue what he really means by koko ni kite, could be "up to now"}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.15,0:32:47.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(372.67,429.13)\bord1\blur1\c&HC7C4C0&}US Treasury Secretary {米国財務長官}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.00,0:32:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,calling for abolition of our high interest rates \Nand dollar appreciation policies. {actually "converting/deviating from"}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.91,0:32:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If this continues, \Nyour re-election is jeopardized.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.66,0:32:53.41,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(373.73,428.06)\bord1\blur1\c&HE7F7FF&}President of the US {大統領}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.72,0:32:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The policies must be abolished. {/converting is unavoidable}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.75,0:32:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Please make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.31,0:33:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrange a meeting with the FRB chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.67,0:33:07.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(375.33,418.47)\fs30\bord1\blur1}September 17th, 11:20 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.67,0:33:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Ministry of Finance secretary \Ndoesn't have any trips abroad scheduled for this week?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.35,0:33:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just for this week, \Nbut for the next month or so!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.75,0:33:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, Taihei have put together a "Currency Market Project Team," with that girl Matsumoto at its nucleus,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.19,0:33:25.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs20\bord1\blur1\pos(382.8,436.06)}Goyo Trading, Business HQ Manager's Office {五洋物産業務本部長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.90,0:33:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they're actively prying into things?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.19,0:33:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We've nothing to fear so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.03,0:33:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're merely scavenging for intel \Nfrom the lower ranks of the Finance Ministry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.70,0:33:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. The businesses are also hurriedly soliciting \Ntheir right to pay this fiscal year's import fees in dollars. {TLC, lit is "dollar allowances for import fees" but I've no clue; also unsure hashiri here is "trying to obtain"; assumed dorateate to be something about interest rate differential, but still doesn't make no sense because it's the "dollar earnings of the import fees" and not the other way around} {/It's typical time of the year for companies to run about, paying the import fees on their earnings in dollar. - variant that I came up first but which is equally a guess; don't seem to find this in manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.58,0:33:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's best that we also keep an eye \Non what the upper echelon is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.46,0:33:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.46,0:33:51.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(378,424.87)}September 17th, Tuesday, 1:05 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.34,0:33:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.53,0:33:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako, it's from the US. A collect call.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.97,0:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.94,0:34:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Matsumoto speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.31,0:34:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Birdwatcher. \NIt's midnight on my end.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.79,0:34:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fishing enthusiast acts a little strange, \Nso I thought I should let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.25,0:34:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Every week, our fishing enthusiast \Ngoes on a round trip to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.10,0:34:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I reached out to the pilot of his charter plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.25,0:34:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Turns out, he doesn't have anything planned \Nfor the upcoming weekend - from 21st to 22nd of September.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.50,0:34:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when I tried to inquire with the company \Nmanaging Fishing Enthusiast's mountain villa,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.59,0:34:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that he might not come there again this season.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.52,0:34:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At least, that's how his wife put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.86,0:34:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... So suspicious. {TLC, no clue, could be "two ways (e.g. of interpreting a word); two kinds; two types"; could be "smells [fishy]", later also used as "suspicious" so probs alright}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.82,0:34:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The river in that area only has the fishing season opened \Nuntil September 25th.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.65,0:34:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This week is his last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.78,0:34:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unlikely that a maniac such as him would miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.78,0:34:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.54,0:34:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The long-anticipated storm is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.78,0:35:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You really didn't have to call a meeting \Nso early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.53,0:35:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I will start with the conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.53,0:35:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,For our tomorrow's newsletter:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.09,0:35:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"Towards the end of this week,{unsure it's asu} \Na multinational group of high-ranking financial officials
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.63,0:35:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,would be very likely to come together for a meeting, \Nto discuss the currency questions."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.05,0:35:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the announcement I came up with. {/that's what info we'll be spreading}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.48,0:35:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When putting together the fragmented data \Nthat was coming our way,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.63,0:35:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly arrive to any other conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.82,0:35:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.35,0:35:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither the minister of finance, nor the secretary, ​
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.18,0:35:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not even the Bank of Japan president \Nhave any plans to travel abroad.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.15,0:35:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, in all the previous instances, \Nwhenever a currency meeting was to be held,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.06,0:35:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd always be some sign beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.32,0:35:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If we only draw conclusions from precedents, \Nthen what is the purpose of our business at all? {/If things were done by precedent, there would be no need for our business.}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.63,0:35:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're acting with utmost care, so as not to let \Nthe Market Circles get wind of what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.63,0:35:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto... If you to steer it with great swings, \Nsuch as this news,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.69,0:36:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the vessel which is our consulting business, \Nwill turn to shipwreck in no time. {lit: "if you row with this important info ..." although not sure this is kogu}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.13,0:36:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Diving headlong without testing the waters... {being excessively cautious; knocking on a strong stone bridge before crossing it​}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.40,0:36:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager! In a highly volatile world that is the currency market, is there really such a thing as safe waters?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.39,0:36:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to help, \Ntighten the observation on our targets. {lit: draw a mark, later she uses that word to say "observe/spy on"}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.16,0:36:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Install a permanent surveillance \Nover the Ministry of Finance secretary's house. {TLC, Very unsure, lit may be "do the thing about as much as sticking/glueing to ...'s house."}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.85,0:36:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, I've read the newsletter!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.85,0:36:22.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(374.27,425.4)\fs25\bord1\blur1}September 19th, Thursday. 10:45 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.42,0:36:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We recommend against holding on to large quantities of American Government Bonds through this weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.63,0:36:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Such was the advice given to Taihei Group companies,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.47,0:36:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but personally, I think it'd be better if you sell \Nat least half of your holdings and convert it to yens. {/what you have on hands}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.64,0:36:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.63,0:36:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust your judgment \Nand will take a chance on your company's intel. {unsure why he says hitotsu}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.40,0:36:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But if some other intel comes to light, \Nplease be sure to let me know immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.14,0:36:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For a small-size financial institution, \Nthis is a matter of life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.63,0:36:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.48,0:36:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,For the moment, we're making every effort\Nto back up that intel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.66,0:36:59.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(381.73,421.13)}September 20th, Friday. 11:40 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.46,0:37:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, I'm going out for a private game of golf, so you'll have to excuse me for not meeting you in the morning. {TLC, no clue what's that asamawari/asamairi}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.17,0:37:04.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\bord1\blur1\pos(379.6,433.93)}Finance Ministry Secretary's house {大蔵省、財務官 自宅}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.42,0:37:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,With a lovely Ginza lady as your opponent, by any chance?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.62,0:37:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Playing golf with a Ginza hostess? Hm. A fine diversion for a man of his position. Very well. Dismissed for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.27,0:37:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy from Goyo received a dismissal already.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.84,0:37:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, let's pull out too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But Sawako told us to peer our eyes into it \Nuntil the morning. {again, "draw a mark"}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.57,0:37:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmpf! It's been two nights already \Nthat we had to spend in the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.85,0:37:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave this to you tonight.\NGood night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.61,0:37:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Manager!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.41,0:37:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Yuki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.23,0:37:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Provisions for the front line. {visiting soldiers at the front to provide comfort; visit to (gift for) persons hard at work as a sign of support}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.60,0:37:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,About time! {guess, I'm suspecting some analogue of itadakimasu, TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.96,0:37:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hide! {guess as well, TLC}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.05,0:38:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Did he just pack his things and leave? {unsure why he says "only"}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.28,0:38:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.53,0:38:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Better call Sawako now.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.21,0:38:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Came back to pick up his suitcase? Roger that. \NKeep a lookout on that position. {mark again}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.00,0:38:29.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(379.06,425.4)}September 21st, Saturday. 7:05 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.76,0:38:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.64,0:38:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,According to Ueda's phone report,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.70,0:38:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,both the minister of finance and the secretary \Ngot into the car, wearing golf uniforms. {hope}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.68,0:38:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Though their alleged destination was Narita Country Golf Club, they're definitely going to New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.73,0:38:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.82,0:38:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wouldn't have been for a glimpse of that suitcase, \Nyou could really think they're going to play golf.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.24,0:39:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The only question now, \Nhow would their final agreement look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.39,0:39:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,First and foremost, they're going to discuss \Na decrease in American interest rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.67,0:39:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,With American interest rates being so high, every other nation is concentrating its investments in the US,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.73,0:39:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,resulting in dollar appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.76,0:39:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If they manage to reach a groundbreaking agreement,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.51,0:39:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it would mean all the nations involved \Nwill try to jointly manipulate the currency market.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.93,0:39:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, a simultaneous intervention?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.68,0:39:25.81,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(393.99,431.26)\frz0.004639}September 22nd, Sunday. New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.81,0:39:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It became an impediment to many economics of the world, \Nso a correction to excessive dollar appreciation is needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.78,0:39:29.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(375,425)\fs34\bord1\blur1} Plaza Hotel {プラザホテル}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.73,0:39:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The US had already stepped up \Nwith one possible countermeasure. {no clue why only one, also no clue what's this youin, neither "preparation; arrangements; provision; getting ready; laying out (e.g. a meal)" nor "main cause; primary factor" makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.95,0:39:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this proposal is contingent \Non the agreement and cooperation
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.08,0:39:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,between the monetary authorities \Nof all countries concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.95,0:39:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The upcoming conference should become a forum \Nfor the most frank discussion of this issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.96,0:39:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the US is taking it seriously this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.50,0:39:52.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}G5 conference held in New York! {G5ニューヨークで開催}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.00,0:39:53.21,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}US corrects high interest rate policy! {米国、高金利政策是正！}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.21,0:39:54.80,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}Agreement for a coordinated currency market intervention in developed countries! {先進国の為替市場に協調介入合意!}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.60,0:40:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before the last weekend, the Taihei Group \Nconverted half of their dollar holdings into yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.18,0:40:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you been doing all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.64,0:40:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,General manager, I hate to echo your words, \Nbut in all such occasions up until now,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.61,0:40:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,resisting the authorities' intervention \Nwas common sense, as it's a lot more profitable. {TLC, no clue what  he means, assumed it's kinda a signle nation's authorities who are supposed to resist it tho again I don't see how it's possible}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.48,0:40:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think even a G5 agreement has the power \Nto reverse the dollar appreciation trend in one fell swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.74,0:40:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that to say that by not selling dollars \Nlast week, the Goyo Group
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.62,0:40:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was actually holding back \Nto avoid unnecessary risks? {/chase after}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.50,0:40:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for all your trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.50,0:40:33.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(385,434)\bord1\blur1}September 23rd, Autumnal Equinox Day. 1:15 P.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.92,0:40:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, Chief of Taihei Bank Currency Market Nakayama \Ngot a call from the Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.51,0:40:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He's meeting someone at 3 o'clock, \Nin front of the fountain at the Hibiya Park! {doesn't make sense that bank of japan calls like that and says "i want to meet you in the park to explain why you should help depreciate dollar" but I see no other explanation}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.51,0:40:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? The foreigners are busy at work, \Neven when it's national holiday in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.68,0:40:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Bank of Japan is also taking it seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.25,0:40:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine, the currency market tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.35,0:40:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,will turn into a dogfight \Nbetween the speculators and the currency authorities.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.27,0:40:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our Bank of Japan \Nis to proclaim an unprecedented market intervention.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.28,0:40:59.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(383.86,437.66)}September 24th, Tuesday. 7:45 A.M.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.86,0:41:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, {in NY }the New York Federal Reserve Bank, \Ntogether with the FRG Federal Reserve
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.28,0:41:03.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs22\bord1\blur1\pos(370.53,436.06)}Bank of Japan, Foreign Currency Division Chief {日本銀行、外国局為替課長}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.87,0:41:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,started selling dollars en masse \Nas agreed previously.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.04,0:41:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of that, \Nthe yen rose from 242 yen to 225 yen at one point.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.53,0:41:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our duty is to inherit that baton \Nand solidify the ongoing trend for the yen appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.78,0:41:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the total turnover of intervention \Nexceeds the $1 billion mark, it doesn't concern us!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.29,0:41:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to sell the devil out of it. {/sell until the very end}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.53,0:41:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.04,0:41:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The price is approaching 229 yen 70 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.05,0:41:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The dollar is put under a surprisingly strong pressure. {no clue why he says unexpectedly if dropping dollar was exactly what they aimed for, could be that by pressure he means "dollar is still rising"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.05,0:41:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The billing companies are having a field day after this. {TLC, NO CLUE! 請求会社あたりが決済資金用の会に出ているな - Lit: "every claim/request/billing company is going out on a meeting concerning settlement (of an account); liquidation of debts; payment funds; capital​" - what I have now is an absolute guess, the best I could stretch this to is "[because so many companies are buying dollar today], the companies doing the billing and accounting would go out to collect the settlement funds for those transactions" even if I fully understand it doesn't make no sense because the stock exchange billing doesn't work this way; the other possibility I was considering is "the companies making a claim [on the shares] are going to have internal meetings used for withdrawing/collecting settlement deposits/allowance"; could even be something like "hasty/rash companies are going to have to take a loan to use it as settlement funds"; doesn't seem to be in manga}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.61,0:41:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bank of Japan begins its first round of intervention \Nany minute now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.10,0:41:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Gone up a bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.10,0:41:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's Bank of Japan. \NOnly about 10,000,000 dollars this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.29,0:41:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.36,0:41:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The yen went down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.62,0:41:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,On Sydney market that starts trading first, the dollar appreciation is also 3 yens above the New York's level. {guess, very unsure it's "san en", although }
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.18,0:42:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is quickly turning into a forced hand market... {strength market\NArtificially forming a market price by repeatedly forcibly buying and selling with the power of funds . - https://www.weblio.jp/content/%E8%85%95%E5%8A%9B%E7%9B%B8%E5%A0%B4 - I don't seem to find a matching term in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.39,0:42:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,231 yen 20 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.18,0:42:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the Bank of Japan directly intervenes, \Nit's no big deal at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.44,0:42:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ueda, even though the G5 prediction turned out true, \Nthe dollar market price hasn't gone down one bit!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.24,0:42:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I tried selling more dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.20,0:42:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But shortly after, just in time for the morning \Ntrade session closure, I bought them back!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.45,0:42:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, the market is going through the stage \Nof probing into the authorities' preparedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.08,0:42:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The trend is definitely changing in the afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.83,0:42:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true? \NIs that something I can fully trust? {/can I depend/trust that}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.99,0:42:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling dollars is the only way now! {TLC, no clue what he means by "here's the dollar selling only way; only means/doing alone; doing single-handed; monopoly​"}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.13,0:42:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir!{hai?} It's back to the 230 yen level!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.51,0:42:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the authorities \Nwill spare no coin to have it their way. {弾に糸目をつけない}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.07,0:42:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of dollars bought, \Nthey keep flooding the market with selling offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.52,0:42:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, even the oil companies started selling!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.02,0:42:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're anticipating the dollar depreciation? {lower future quotations}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.14,0:42:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! The mood has changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.65,0:42:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.13,0:43:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell more! More! Sell it all out! {sell on a large scale}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.64,0:43:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over, at 230 yen 10 sen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.49,0:43:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yen appreciation compared to pre-weekend level \Nis at 11 yen 90 sen! {https://www.macrotrends.net/2550/dollar-yen-exchange-rate-historical-chart - might be a bit confusing to understand, but yen was 242.05 before the intervention}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.94,0:43:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you make sure to repair this damage in the future! {actually "We're going to make sure we get this loss back." but what does it mean? he's gonna fee tsugawa for that or what? could be "make sure you return this money to us with your work in the future or smt"}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.26,0:43:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This new enterprise of ours took off pretty well. {lit: as new business, good performance}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.92,0:43:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, even you couldn't help \Ntaking your hat off to Matsumoto, I believe. {to concede defeat; to surrender; to take one's hat off (to someone)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.17,0:43:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.80,0:43:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This 24-hour lookout \Nover Ministry of Finance Secretary's house...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.34,0:43:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I thought that was going a bit too far at first, {TLC, no clue what's this joukyou or else dunno what he means by "I thought I was in a bit of a situation. "}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.12,0:43:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually, it turned out to be a decisive factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.51,0:43:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.60,0:43:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The total trading turnover today \Nwas over $4.7 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.19,0:43:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly one-third of those dollars \Nwere sold by the Bank of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.24,0:43:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Our foreign-exchange reserves \Namount to about $27.5 billion, {Foreign-exchange reserves (also called forex reserves or FX reserves) in a strict sense are 'only' the foreign currency deposits and bonds held by central banks and monetary authorities. However, the term in popular usage commonly includes foreign exchange and gold, special drawing rights (SDRs) and International Monetary Fund (IMF) reserve positions. This broader figure is more readily available, but it is more accurately termed official international reserves or international reserves.} {I hab no idea why he suddenly talks of that btw}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.03,0:43:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,while the combined global stock trading turnover \Nadds up to $150-200 billion a day. {stocking up on; hoarding}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.74,0:43:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With the current system in place, the currency's strength is defined by the whims of its market price. {not sure what she means by "to go in the direction of; to proceed toward; to proceed according to; to repair to; to betake oneself to"}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.71,0:43:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.23,0:44:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The market's only master \Nis the market itself, agreed? {相場のことは相場に聞け - ask the market about the market}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.90,0:44:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yukie, how can you know that? {TLC, absolutely no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.92,0:44:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make fun of me, by extension,\Nyou do it to everyone in Business Headquarters! {lit is "don't make fun of me, I'm with this a one member of ..." but I have no clue what she means and why he looks shocked at everyone next}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.30,0:44:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeeh?! {guess}
