Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.32,0:44:39.36,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\bord1\blur1\pos(374.8,414.2)\frz359.3}London, Thames Riverside {ロンドン・テムズ河畔}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.36,0:44:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, Diana.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.84,0:44:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Charles...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.00,0:44:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Diana?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.68,0:44:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I-In the river! {miru?}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.44,0:45:04.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz0\fs25\bord1\blur1}Mysterious body floating in the Thames River!? {テムズ河に浮かぶ疑問符！？ - actually 疑問符 is question mark but I don't see how it makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.18,0:45:08.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}Puzzling Drowned Body is Enrique, Banco da Vinci President!?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.19,0:45:12.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord\blur\c&H43441E&\3c&HEAEBDF&}Manager's Office {業務本部長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.19,0:45:16.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\bord1\blur1\pos(384.93,413.67)\frz0.07602}Goyo Manufacturing, Business HQ Manager's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.41,0:45:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, this seems serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.19,0:45:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it? You look hot and bothered.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.17,0:45:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enrique has been found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.02,0:45:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.66,0:45:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been some time since he last \Nmade contact with us, and now - this mess. {mess; sorry state; plight; sad sight​}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.66,0:45:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"The man is believed to be the Da Vinci Bank president, \Nwho had gone missing and a search request was filed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.99,0:45:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Last seen 10 days ago in his Milan residence.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.17,0:45:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, he suddenly disappeared."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.91,0:45:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit... Even though they never mention \Nany traces of suicide or murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.14,0:45:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only believe that he was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.72,0:45:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... Did Enrique cross paths \Nwith someone dangerous? {lit is "cross a dangerous bridge" usually it's a proverb meaning take risks/break the law, but here I think he means in both senses because river; was "Was Enrique\Nlikely to burn\Nhis bridges\Nbehind him" in TL but I think he misunderstood it}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.18,0:45:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, his Banco da Vinci was among Italy's \Nleading financial institutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.58,0:45:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He was also an important figure \Nin Milan's business circles. Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.33,0:45:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Just... What?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.71,0:45:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lately, internal power struggles plague Vatican.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.00,0:46:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Rumors of him being involved reached me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.47,0:46:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Vatican?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.41,0:46:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.70,0:46:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Da Vinci's still liable to our underwriting! {tlc, honestly, I've been grinding against this one line for 3 hours or so and I still don't understand what it says. Has to be "...の債権を引き受けて信用を付け" but every part of it can have multiple meanings all of which make some sense but none makes sense fully. I assumed it to be "we have taken it on ourselves to underwrite davinci's credit/give credit to davinci/guarantee credits that davinci gives, by doing so, bulding /giving/taking credit/trust" - but why the fuck would some japanese consulting firm underwrite a random italian bank???}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.70,0:46:12.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,400)\fs30\bord1\blur1\frz0\pos(387.06,420.6)}Taihei Finance, Business HQ Manager's Office {太平商事・業務本部長室}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.09,0:46:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You were the one who suggested that we tap into \NVatican's vast funds that da Vinci operates! {honestly not sure what to make of kurikomu/kuikomu}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.18,0:46:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly to London, Milan or wherever \Nand figure things out personally! {/handle}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.84,0:46:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.63,0:46:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{?}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.38,0:46:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How careless can you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.71,0:46:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But Manager, it wasn't my fault this time! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.90,0:46:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.98,0:46:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.15,0:46:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with that attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.27,0:46:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How can one be named after a beautiful river of Mikawa, \Nand still be a stinky creek? {there's no such real river as mikawa, also it's last name and not given name so I don't really understand what she's saying but it's not that important so idc}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.03,0:46:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.03,0:46:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.03,0:46:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.03,0:46:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the stinky creek again?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.62,0:46:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No... I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.99,0:46:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I should {\i1}stick{\i0} the documents together \Nand not {\i1}crease{\i0} them. {lit: picking up the docs takes the guts too}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.01,0:46:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, enough incorrigible gibberish.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.22,0:46:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, book me the earliest possible \Nticket to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.56,0:46:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.38,0:46:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.92,0:47:01.42,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}Banco Da Vinci President Enrique?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.43,0:47:06.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1}Banco Da Vinci President Enrique?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.56,0:47:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If it isn't Mikawa from Taihei!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.58,0:47:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.05,0:47:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you heading to? {business trip; official trip}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.48,0:47:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,L-Los Angeles. What about you? {not sure}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.00,0:47:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, just a short trip to Singapore.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.16,0:47:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.12,0:48:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Weren't you going to Los Angeles?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.98,0:48:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you were heading for Singapore...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.88,0:48:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I... Need to go to London as well. \NJust a small detour. {/got a small business there}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.63,0:48:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... That's an interesting coincidence. \NIt's the same for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.05,0:48:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You sly dog. {sly dog; sly old fox; sly fox; cunning devil; sly person/tanuki}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.51,0:48:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You sneaky fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.02,0:48:41.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\bord1\blur1\pos(374.27,401.94)}A few months prior in Milan, Italy {数ヶ月前・・・イタリア、ミラノ}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.96,0:48:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you can excuse me for using my own apartment \Nto discuss business with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.13,0:48:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I absolutely wanted to introduce you \Nwith the genuine Italian hospitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.62,0:49:01.63,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs30\bord1\blur1\pos(398.79,345.97)}Banco da Vinci Chief Bond Dealer Gelsomina {バンコ・ダビンチ銀行チーフディラージェルソミーナ}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.42,0:49:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if someone told me \NBanco da Vinci's chief bond dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.35,0:49:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,could be this beautiful, I wouldn't believe them. {/Well I was astonished to discover ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.65,0:49:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate your attention. {細やかな心遣いに感謝します volume 1 page 227}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.03,0:49:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope for nothing less \Nthan fruitful negotiations. {unsure what he means - これで話がまとまれば言うことなし… ですがね}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.64,0:49:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can assure you we'll achieve that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.04,0:49:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Our investment efficiency stands its ground \Nagainst any other bank in Europe. {not losing out (to); holding one's own (against); comparing favorably (with); being a fair match (for)}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.42,0:49:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Concluding profitable deals is our priority. {/we never make a deal that'll bring a loss}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.15,0:49:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I gathered \Nfrom the statistics you provided. One more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.30,0:49:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the current situation \Nof monetary revolution unfolding in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.14,0:49:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the strategy your bank intends to employ? {現在世界的に進展している金融革命の中で貴行がどのような戦略をとろろとしていそのか}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.35,0:49:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of my visit today is to learn that. {今回はそれをお聞きしたくて伺ったのです}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.14,0:49:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to reassure you on that matter as well. {それに関しても自信があります}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.31,0:49:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.48,0:49:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.67,0:49:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to achieve a lasting business relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.00,0:49:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you think it's essential \Nto build a good personal partnership first? {末永くお取引いただくためには…まず良きパートナーシップを築くことが大切なのではありません}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.02,0:50:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we make ourselves comfortable tonight? {/I want you to take your time and feel at home}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.91,0:50:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A marvelous idea for the night. {/this night would become wonderful}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.05,0:50:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's also Gelsomina...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.67,0:50:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What... Gelsomina?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.71,0:50:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Could that possibly be \NGelsomina of Banco da Vinci?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.75,0:50:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.07,0:50:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, don't you mean to say, \Nyou're also going there because of {this Geezer }Enrique? {no clue what he means by "enrique's cunning old man"; before he called mikawa tanuki so likely he means "you're enrique's pet dog/sly agent" but mikawa isn't exactly that old yet to be a jiji and besides in this very sentence he uses respectable language so why would he suddenly offend mikawa in this very sentence?}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.67,0:50:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you in Goyo too...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.44,0:50:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you know - apparently, we're going to London \Nfor the very same reason, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.68,0:50:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you, Enrique...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.93,0:50:44.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord1\blur1\pos(420,410)}Banco da Vinci, Milan
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.19,0:50:50.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs35\bord1\blur1\pos(381.2,413.14)}Banco Da Vinci President{toudori} Enrique
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.90,0:50:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I take it our chief bond dealer explained to you \Nour bank's conditions in all details, Signor Mikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.71,0:50:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. All in all, it seems like a sensible line of action. {/line (of action); position; approach; policy; principle}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.74,0:50:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,After I consult with Tokyo, I hope we can come \Nto an agreement within the next few days. {/conclusion} {東京と諮って\N一両日中に結論を出したいと思います vol 1 p. 233}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.70,0:51:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All of our bank's regular customers are successful companies, prominent on the international level.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.27,0:51:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The safety of their assets is a given.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.91,0:51:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our plans also include \Nopening a branch in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.37,0:51:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that in doing so we will expedite greatly \Na closer cooperation with Taihei.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.74,0:51:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.53,0:51:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're at it, President Enrique,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.72,0:51:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wondering if the rumors of your institution's \Nstrong influence on Christian Capitals were true. {/religion-related funds}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.16,0:51:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an unwritten rule among financiers \Nnot to disclose anything specific about their clients. {actually says "specific clients" but does that mean just selling out your non-special clients is alright???}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.19,0:51:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, our bank made it pretty big \Non the Italian market.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.75,0:51:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave the rest to your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.24,0:51:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,For sure, by nibbling your way \Ninto an organization that exclusive,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.97,0:51:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or appointing an exquisite beauty \Non a position pivotal to the bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.77,0:51:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you've proven yourself \Nan outstanding bank president. {Mrエンリケは並の頭取ではないと感心していますよ - no ordinary}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.02,0:51:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Should even you harbor a fondness for someone from our staff, that's none of my business, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.28,0:52:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Susceptibility to the woman's charms \Nis innate to Japanese and to Italians alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.23,0:52:15.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs40\bord1\blur1\pos(390.79,413.67)}Goyo Trading London Office
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.79,0:52:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Tsugawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.79,0:52:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you learn anything new?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.56,0:52:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They've confirmed his identity. \NIt was Enrique, beyond any doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.82,0:52:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tentatively, the presumed cause of death is suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.14,0:52:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A suicide, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.80,0:52:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're still feverishly gathering information in the City, \Nbut no definite conclusion has been reached yet. {no clue what he mens by "手を打つ"; also why he says シティ, because it's certainly not city, later they use it in a sense "[their] company" so could be citigroup.jp? also: "The City - A popular name for the historic section of London , the City of London , and the financial district located there."}
Comment: 0,0:52:40.80,0:52:47.73,Sign,,0,0,0,,Note: "The City" = financial district of London
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.73,0:52:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There's just that rumor, saying Banco da Vinci's \Nsubsidiaries in Luxemburg and Liechtenstein
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.87,0:52:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have hoarded large amounts of nonperforming loans.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.11,0:52:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.24,0:53:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to that, \Nthere's also a story that money was flowing to the mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.33,0:53:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So... Did you manage to grasp \Nda Vinci's state of affairs?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.85,0:53:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... We have the latest fiscal report.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.17,0:53:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But da Vinci has, beside its main body,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.75,0:53:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple holding companies \Nand foreign local affiliates.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.26,0:53:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With such an inscrutable spiderweb of subsidiaries, \Nnobody can grasp the actual state of affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.74,0:53:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the City pulls all strings at once, \Nda Vinci would go under, wouldn't it? {very unsure about "all muscles move" but assumed he still talking about the spiderweb and its strings}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.45,0:53:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,All the bankers agree that in the event of a bank run \Nthe bankruptcy seems unavoidable.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.78,0:53:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}that{\i0} bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.25,0:53:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't know for sure yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.78,0:53:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But if even just one of those rumors \Nflying around proves true,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.29,0:53:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that would seem quite possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.79,0:53:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely enough, \Nda Vinci has some backers, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.79,0:53:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. You mean Vatican, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.52,0:53:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Though they go to great lengths to hide it, {cover (e.g. for illegal activity); front; guise}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.86,0:54:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that Vatican is among that bank's \Nlargest stockholders is undeniable.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.40,0:54:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the Vatican connection was apparently leveraged \Nto allocate huge loans to a paper company,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.35,0:54:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that were later written off as unrecoverable.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.20,0:54:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the mafia comes into play... {unsure what he means "and if mafia intervenes there..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.46,0:54:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the chances of recovering our assets are slim?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.36,0:54:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... Unfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.13,0:54:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it was a comparatively minor investment, \Nso our losses are sustainable.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.95,0:54:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, in the City's inner circles, \Nconcerns are raised over a possible chain bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.89,0:54:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you, Enrique...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.02,0:54:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time I was meeting with him, \Nhis tail was already on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.48,0:54:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He's {\i1}had{\i0} me \Nwhile feigning ignorance. {innocent look; nonchalant look; look of ignorance; air of innocence}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.88,0:54:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our losses are less than that of Goyo?" \NImbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.31,0:54:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that make our own situation any better?!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.51,0:54:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's inexcusable...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.82,0:55:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the internal opposition to our company's current investment strategy is stronger than ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.21,0:55:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts way more than any financial losses!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.80,0:55:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.36,0:55:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, I despise this guy. \NBut today, even I feel sorry for him!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.71,0:55:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Department chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.11,0:55:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be premature to conclude \Nthat nothing can be salvaged? {/that everything is lost}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.80,0:55:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.86,0:55:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for butting in, {/chiming in while being the third party}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.79,0:55:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't you expect the Vatican to try to come \Nto their relief, in one way or another?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.29,0:55:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The papal court operates vastly larger funds \Nthan even Japan's national budget. {I doubt it but that's what she says}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.39,0:55:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If it gets involved in a financial scandal, \Nresulting in a collapse of even one bank from the group,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.58,0:55:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll end up losing the trust \Nof the believers from all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.53,0:55:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... However, some influential British banks\Nare already cashing out their bonds. {hope he means this by "withdrawing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.65,0:55:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If only 2 or 3 more banks follow, \Nit'll be the end of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.91,0:55:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have a small window of opportunity, \Nbefore they are completely out of business. {/outed}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.30,0:56:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If we play our cards right, \Nit may be enough to get things straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.42,0:56:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.93,0:56:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. You can give it a try. \NSomething in your words inspires confidence. {I hope he means "[this affair/assignment] is yours/you can have it"}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.82,0:56:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I also want Mikawa to follow you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.80,0:56:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,However! We can't afford another blunder here.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.43,0:56:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Take every precaution before acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.33,0:56:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.44,0:56:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard it from the news on TV yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.54,0:56:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They apprehended some big shot \Nof the Italian financial world involved in this affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.49,0:56:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard of this news.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.99,0:56:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,May I add, that's one baffling affair.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.79,0:56:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... Europe's financial world is in turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.72,0:56:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Add to that the mafia link and the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.93,0:56:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A {unimaginable }rumor is circulating \Nthat it was the business circles' doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.50,0:56:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can't really blame Mikawa. {no clue what she means by "rather/better"}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.23,0:56:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This Tsugawa from Goyo Group \Ngot caught up in it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.11,0:56:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems that Enrique was one sly daredevil. {strong-willed person; old hand; shrewd rascal; wily fox; desperate character; formidable woman}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.29,0:56:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of international finances is murky waters. {veritable pandemonium; large number of people plotting and doing evil; creepy characters roaming about}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.70,0:57:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd known stories of fraud \Nfor as long as it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.04,0:57:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're at it, how exactly \Ndo you intend to sort out the da Vinci affair?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.96,0:57:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my Harvard Business School classmates \Nnow works for a major American bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.26,0:57:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She had since become \Nthe senior economist in the Manhattan Trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.77,0:57:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She is currently in Japan for a business trip, \Nso I thought I'd ask her for a bit of advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.32,0:57:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see now. \NJapan's Hokuto Finance conglomerate {really hope it's a proper name}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.55,0:57:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,plans to establish a subsidiary in the US? {no idea what they talkin about}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.75,0:57:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew they wanted to branch out into the securities. {still no idea what's this talk and where did it come from; /bonds dealing}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.68,0:57:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What I didn't know is that Taihei are also attempting \Nto tap into the international money flow. {to poke one's nose into another's affairs; to have a hand in; to take a (deep) interest in; to meddle in}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.68,0:57:35.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(379.6,329.44)\fs23\bord1\blur1}Manhattan Trust Bank Senior Economist Anne Marie Taylor {マンハッタントラスト銀行 シニアエコノミスト アンマリーテイラー}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.18,0:57:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time we encountered some unavoidable setbacks. {TLC, no idea what's koutai here tbh, could be "couldn't help ruuning into trouble"}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.53,0:57:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.29,0:57:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Taihei really did the right thing \Nby focusing their attention on Europe over the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.15,0:57:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that to say, \Na financial enterprise founded in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.50,0:57:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can get to work right away, \Ntrading securities and providing banking services?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.20,0:57:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The ultimate destination of this financial revolution \Nis a world with no market restrictions. {she is talking about the removal of the barrier between securities companies and stock market to be precise}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.68,0:58:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan and the US are also on their way \Nto becoming very Europe-like in this respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.80,0:58:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And to expedite that process, \Nstudying the European experience is not a half-bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.36,0:58:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say so, we're having to start from a complete zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.72,0:58:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sawako. If Taihei are seriously committed to it, \NI'm willing to lend you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.30,0:58:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The cobbler knows his last. {lit is "best moch are in the mochi shop" meaning it's best to employ expert for the job but I can't think of an appropriate engish proverb}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.74,0:58:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our company is the perfect hub \Nfor all kinds of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.24,0:58:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, Banco da Vinci's \NLuxembourg subsidiary declared bankruptcy.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.73,0:58:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. This means the book is closed on the da Vinci Group. {tbh no clue what's ikkan}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.25,0:58:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The Milan headquarters still conducts business as usual, \Nbut they're on borrowed time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.93,0:58:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the moment is right. {right time; favourable opportunity (favorable)}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.02,0:58:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.69,0:58:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, I'm leaving for Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.22,0:58:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to da Vinci personally?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.03,0:58:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They must be at sixes and sevens right about now, \Nwith no time to meet small fry such as us.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.76,0:59:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, I thought I'd go there \Nto attend Enrique's funeral service.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.95,0:59:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It took them longer than expected to return the body, \Nbut it seems, tomorrow they're finally going to bury him.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.17,0:59:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Since when do you care for his funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.78,0:59:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He put one over on you, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.48,0:59:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thought I should pay my respects. { at least posthumously}{actually no idea why she says "assume the posture of praying; to press the palms and fingers of both hands together; to do reverence (e.g. before a statue of the Buddha); to pay one's respects to his dead face" so stealing from manga TL here}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.78,0:59:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord is my shepherd; {https://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=Psalm+23&version=MEV}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.78,0:59:23.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,300)\fs25\bord1\blur1\pos(379.6,283.6)}Cemetery on the outskirts of Milan, Italy {イタリアミラノ郊外の墓地}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.65,0:59:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall not want.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.34,0:59:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes me lie down in green pastures;
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.75,0:59:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He leads me beside still waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.66,0:59:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I pray that you guide his soul to heaven \Nand there grant him peace. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.76,0:59:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.23,0:59:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pass this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.32,0:59:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Senorita, did you say "Matsumoto?"
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.17,0:59:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.33,1:00:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the midst of this hubbub, you're the first one \Nto come see me personally like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.25,1:00:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of respect for this letter of introduction, \NI'll hear you out.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.88,1:00:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Be mindful though, \Nwhat you expect me to do is probably impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.35,1:00:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wield the power \Nyour introducer thinks I have.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.41,1:00:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm all ears.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.40,1:00:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope coming all the way to Zürich for this \Nwasn't too much of a bother...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.40,1:00:34.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs45\bord1\blur1\pos(377.46,411.01)}Zürich, Switzerland
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.29,1:00:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mention it. \NFor me, it's an unexpected but welcome vacation. {/unsolicited}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.13,1:00:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I'm more than happy to be of service.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.91,1:00:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Meeting with that man they call the Agent of Vatican,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.30,1:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,would've been impossible without that Manhattan Trust \Nletter of introduction you gave me. {relly hope they mean this by mantora}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.93,1:00:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how to thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.42,1:00:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"Give and take."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.05,1:00:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I'm also counting \Non your help in the near future.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.92,1:00:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.57,1:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is, starting next month, I'll be working \Nas a deputy manager of M.T. branch office in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.07,1:01:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being transferred to Tokyo! {/appointed}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.82,1:01:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? I'll help in every way I can \Nonce you're in Tokyo!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.49,1:01:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's still small potatoes \Ncompared to what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.51,1:01:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Word is, that man is a mafia bigwig.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.25,1:01:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how did it go? {hope she measns this}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.94,1:01:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations successful...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.63,1:01:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Or so I want to think. {hope}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.80,1:01:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have some practical odds and ends to sort out,\Nbut presently, Vatican is in no shape to be bullish. {REALLY hope she means this, was "also seems to be in pretty good shape" in TL}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.47,1:01:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, you're visiting their stronghold today? {probably by "stronghold; inner citadel; base; headquarters" she means "heartland/something that has to be conquered"}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.42,1:01:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. To the head office of Göttfert Bank I go. {ゴットフェルト - could be gutfeld/gottfert or w/e but idc}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.83,1:01:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, our company's desire \Nis not the acquisition of your bank,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.82,1:01:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but of your talents. {really hard to do this right in english, because she is trying to be serious and business-like but also a bit obsequious at the same time, lit is "we want you"}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.48,1:01:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In the financial world headed towards \Nliberalization and internationalization, {added}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.46,1:02:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan is woefully behind the times.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.49,1:02:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you, tempered by rough seas of Zürich's finances, \Nwith judgment that's sharp at all times, {to be shrewd; to be sharp; to keep your wits about you; to pluck out the eye of a live horse​}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.49,1:02:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whom I trust to guide Japan through it. {/I would definitely want to ask for your guidance}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.50,1:02:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I humbly ask you to give Taihei a chance. {/help}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.96,1:02:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... {guess}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.96,1:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... {guess}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.82,1:02:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to announce our decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.01,1:02:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our bank's desire is not to help out Taihei Finance.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.89,1:02:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.66,1:02:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}is{\i0} our desire to make you happy \Nby any means necessary. {very liberal and I don't like it but otherwise it won't be a throwback and won't retain the structure, lit: if it's for you personally, we can do anything}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.00,1:02:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.72,1:02:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you look at this lady who made it big. {/considerable; great; important; significant; a big deal girl}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.44,1:02:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're ever tired of Taihei, \NI'd be willing to take you in anytime.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.62,1:02:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.03,1:03:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! So you've secured an acquisition \Nof da Vinci's subsidiary, Göttfert Bank? {/the prospect of buying ... is confirmed - I think he means "you already negotiated it with their board?"}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.62,1:03:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, we're getting it pretty cheap!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.11,1:03:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, our unrecoverable{added} da Vinci bonds \Nwould be used to cover the part of the purchase cost? Hm! {hope he means this by "will keep on living as part ..."}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.73,1:03:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the da Vinci Group members, Göttfert is the one bank \Nthat sustained the least losses in the recent affair.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.62,1:03:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That was thanks to its Swiss management \Nconducting a sound enterprise.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.18,1:03:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Its board is stuffed \Nwith honest and conscientious people. {good-natured; of good character​ - not sure how it pertains to the case}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.64,1:03:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A bank that combines two functions \Nof a trust company and a securities trader in Europe, {unsure about this trust thing, not usually the word used this way and shintaku can be also "new branch"}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.67,1:03:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to do business for us as a subsidiary \Nis a cherished dream of Japan's banking sector! {think he means "everyone of" but saving CPS}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.09,1:03:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, you got it all to ourselves! {lit: did it}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.72,1:03:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole industry would eat their hearts out! {/be in for a surprise}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.23,1:03:57.76,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs25\bord1\blur1\fade(0,300)}Taihei Finance purchases Göttfert Bank!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.39,1:04:01.75,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,300)\fs25\bord1\blur1}Laying the groundwork for a Merchant Bank?! {preparations; preparatory steps; arrangements; (laying the) groundwork (for)}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.79,1:04:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit... Matsumoto Sawako again!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.54,1:04:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto, please have another glass with us!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.14,1:04:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Words can't express my gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.98,1:04:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was lucky to pull this off.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.63,1:04:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I never expected it to actually go so well.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.94,1:04:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our source in Vatican says \Nthey're scrambling for loans. {/But you've heard what the sources in Vatican are all saying. - he means vatican needs to get into a lot of loans, not sure if I should specify it or not}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.44,1:04:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Göttfert's gonna come out of this \Nwith quite the profit. {lit: ... is a profitable bank isn't it - unsure he meant what I commented in the last line though}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.68,1:04:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. To clean up after the da Vinci affair, \NVatican requires a lot of additional funds.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.12,1:04:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say they're now tens of millions of dollars in debt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.04,1:04:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.25,1:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Da Vinci's beautiful chief bond dealer already inquired \Nif we could hire her to work for Göttfert Bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.46,1:04:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She was so infatuated with Mikawa, after all... {/intimate relationship}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.41,1:04:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Matsumoto!
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.25,1:04:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! He's blushing! Mikawa, \Ndid you really have something with that lady?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.72,1:05:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'd rather you refrain from speculations! {/unnecessary things}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.56,1:05:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But you gotta admit, our company's zaitech efforts \Nwill go a long way after this! {lit: riding a spur}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.69,1:05:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan's financial revolution was implemented \Nas a countermeasure to the first oil shock of 1973. {implemented/enforced/put into practice kinda contradicts the concept of revolution, but that's what he says}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.49,1:05:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Triggered by the large-scale international issuance \Nof bonds and notes, {added because otherwise unclear issuance of what}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.95,1:05:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it served to promote \Nfinancial liberalization and internationalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.39,1:05:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The barrier was gradually lowered \Nbetween the banks and the securities companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.87,1:05:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That new fierce rivalry \Nroused financial world from the slumber.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.35,1:05:43.25,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HF8EDE6&\bord0\blur0.8\1a&H00&\pos(382.26,134.34)}Episode 4 \N {\fs38\blur0.8} Shares: A Market for the New Breed {株式・新人類相場 - https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%96%B0%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E#%E6%96%B0%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E_(%E4%B8%96%E4%BB%A3) - actually not sure what word to use but i can't just go zoomers can i}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.13,1:06:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The year is 1815. The news of Napoleon losing at Waterloo \Nwas caught by the Rothschilds' House before anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.93,1:06:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But by {deliberately }selling British {Government }Bonds at the stock exchange,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.37,1:06:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,they created an illusion of Napoleon winning.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.10,1:06:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bonds nosedived in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.25,1:06:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Realizing it was their time to act, \Nthe Rothschild Family bought up the bonds,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.57,1:06:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,thus laying the groundwork \Nfor becoming the world's wealthiest family,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.71,1:06:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or so says the popular legend. {I think here she uses anecdote as "fallacy/misconception"}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.30,1:06:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.31,1:06:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you bringing up such an ancient story?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.74,1:06:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, when I went to Kabutocho yesterday, \NI couldn't help feeling as if in a time slip, {hope she means this tho lit is "I ended up traveling in time"} {Kabutochō (neighbourhood of Nihonbashi, Tokyo, where the Tokyo Stock Exchange is located)}
Comment: 0,1:06:41.74,1:06:45.46,Sign,,0,0,0,,Note: Kabutocho = Japanese Wall Street {/Tokyo Stock Exchange neighborhood}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.46,1:06:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so the Rothschilds came to mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.94,1:06:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All the extra money freed up across Japan by the lowering of interest rates last year began flowing into Kabutocho.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.21,1:06:51.20,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs50\c&HFFF5E5&\1a&H27&\3c&H2F0D0F&\3a&H9E&\pos(380,395.01)}April 1987
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.55,1:07:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Some estimates place the daily money turnover \Nof this place at 1.5 trillion yen.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.21,1:07:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how Japan achieved its current prosperity, \Nisn't that how saying goes? {unsure what's "only" to do here}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.17,1:07:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is, there's only a handful of {\i1}actually{\i0} \Nliquid stocks that everyone ends up buying and selling. {lit: everyone buys and sells the same stocks}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.86,1:07:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect, it's thanks to those stocks \Nthat I'm able to take my seniors for a drive like this. {no clue what she's talking about, hopefully will become clearer later, probably means she bought this car with stock earnings}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.28,1:07:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You trade stocks too, Yukie? {not sure she means this}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.14,1:07:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Only an idiot would let their money \Ngather dust in the bank. {added, lit is just "depositing money is stupid"}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.78,1:07:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I invested into what I use the most{ at work}! {honestly, this whole convo is driving me crazy, why do you have to talk so cryptic all the time? no idea what's rei here, but it should be something like "by doing this/with this as an example *makes a gesture with her hand* I earned a big sum" - assumed she shows herself talking on the phone, although can't be sure}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.14,1:07:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,NTT stocks?
Comment: 0,1:07:23.14,1:07:24.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,NTT = Nippon Telegraph & Telephone
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.56,1:07:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What I bought for 1,197,000 yen originally\Nnow costs a whopping 3,180,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.39,1:07:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Net income — about 2 million yen,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.84,1:07:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with which I bought this car!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.03,1:07:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yukie, how much money did you receive \Nfrom the company in paychecks during that period?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.49,1:07:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, let me think, maybe just a fraction of two millions... {it gets more fucking confusing with every line passing, the ave. annual salary in 1987 was 3,500,000 yen, how the fuck can it be a fraction of 2 mil? probs she means "I did it in just under 2-3 months" or smt but would have been a lot more reasonable to say "oh, about 2 mil. or so..." so that she's immediately exposed of actually buying it with her honest labor}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.18,1:07:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.46,1:07:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do this to me. \NYou're not allowing me any pleasant dreams at all! {/even though I was finally seeing ...}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.94,1:07:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If even you are trading stocks these days, we must do what it takes to adopt the Portfolio System ASAP. {TLC, unsure what words she says, prolly "we've no choice but hurry up with promoting ..."}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.81,1:07:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.43,1:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Market trends analysis that previously relied on manual labor would instead be performed using a simulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.58,1:08:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Computer software is the way to go \Nfor composing a successful investment plan.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.78,1:08:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I didn't understand a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.35,1:08:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The thought of someone making 2 million on stocks \Nwithout even understanding that is terrifying. {really unsure she means this, as later yukie stops smiling in response}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.92,1:08:18.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\pos(378.53,345.44)}Mitsubishi Trust Bank {actually 五菱信託銀行 not 三菱 but it was apparently done to avoid copyright and I have no idea what to make of 五菱 in japanese}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.46,1:08:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, buy it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.76,1:08:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"Buy what?" \NHinomoto Steel Works, one million shares. {unsure about the first word (could be kai, could be kaiin), volume 3 page 171 of manga}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.43,1:08:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Tozai Insurance bought 3 million shares? {again, hoping this touzai is some given name}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.93,1:08:27.97,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,200)\pos(380,420)\bord1\blur1}Fund Management Department, Goryo Trust {fund management; fund operation} {no clue what's oiwa here, it's just sticks in the middle of nowhere, not seems to make sense neither as the guy's name nor as the organization, and there's no city of such name; replaced with goryo because I still have no clue what's oiwa and these guys eventually work for goryo} {資金運用部 大岩}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.78,1:08:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then make it 3 million for us as well!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.63,1:08:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.88,1:08:32.92,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs40\pos(392.39,413.67)\c&HF9FDF5&\1a&H25&\3c&H2F0D0F&\3a&H7B&}Director Iida {飯田部長 - again, could be company name instead}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.34,1:08:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If this places operates 1.2 trillion yen with just 6 people...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.93,1:08:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes it 200 billion yen per person.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.72,1:08:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,200 billion?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.90,1:08:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're no match for the New Breed. {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E6%96%B0%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E#%E6%96%B0%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E_(%E4%B8%96%E4%BB%A3) - usually used in negative sense like zoomers, but actually maybe he means "they can't catch up with the yunghins", also idk who cant catch up with whom}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.40,1:08:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Director, making fun of us in plain sight again?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.33,1:08:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For us, working here, handling 100 yen \Nand handling tens of billions of yen is the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.11,1:08:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry about a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.61,1:08:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's exactly what worries me — \Nyou guys have no notion of fear. {/how to be afraid}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.09,1:09:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Before dealing in stocks, we got a flair for it, \Ntrading government securities.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.08,1:09:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That confidence is what scares me the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.14,1:09:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this way please.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.16,1:09:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A Portfolio System?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.10,1:09:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In the US, that system had already been adopted \Nby the Merry Lunch Inc. {very stupid name for a company but I've no clue what else メリーランチ could be; I suspect it's another slightly altered name of a real company but I can't exactly point my finger at which one it could be; /Mary Ranch Company}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.80,1:09:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, with an outstanding record.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.45,1:09:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I've also been paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.07,1:09:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But the American market environment \Nis too different from ours. {/circumstances}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.07,1:09:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This era, in which even a female office clerk \Ncan make 2 million in a matter of just a few months — {apparently not in manga, so my best bet: 一応得る/OLがほんの数ヶ月で200万も儲ける時代が いつまでも続くと思いですか?}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.80,1:09:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,do you believe it'll last forever?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.79,1:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good question...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.99,1:09:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If we adjust the US-rooted software \Nto the needs of the Japanese market, {unsure what's  improvement; reform" here}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.38,1:09:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it'll surely be of much practical use.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.03,1:09:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Indeed, it'd take one look at our fund manager \Nto tell that he's but an amateur.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.99,1:09:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But didn't Goryo Trust assign its best fund managers \Nto you, their Institutional Investor?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.46,1:09:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's embarrassing, even.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.34,1:09:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be the Institutional Investor by designation, \Nbut really, we've only ever dealt in bonds.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.48,1:10:01.98,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(367.33,367.29)\bord1\blur1\fs22\q2}Trust Fund = financial body, {freely }operating property and assets of its beneficiaries {/trust bank} {ファンド・トラスト(ファントラ)・信託銀行が自由に運用できる委託金}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.22,1:10:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been less than two years since we incorporated \Nthe stock market into the Trust Fund.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.92,1:10:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it the same for other Institutional Investors too?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.85,1:10:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,All they know is to take after government, \Nnon-life insurance and private insurance firms. {actually sonpo and hoken are both "insurance" so idk what he meant; also no clue why he says "such things as government and damage insurance" because government itself is not even a particiant at the market? TLC. hate this line deeply; lit is "government, damage insurance etc, and insurance companies as well are alike"}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.44,1:10:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're all amateurs, they can't survive without relying on the info they receive from the broker-dealers. {brokerage; brokerage firm; broking house; securities company - could be any of that tbh}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.20,1:10:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it all the more reasons to embrace the Portfolio System that could prove so useful for the Japanese stock market?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.87,1:10:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.32,1:10:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's her, isn't it? \NThe elite female consultant from Taihei Finance.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.96,1:10:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,She graduated abroad from Harvard, all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.17,1:10:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But back in Japan, she's but an ordinary woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.67,1:10:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Word is, she's actually quite the go-getter.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.29,1:10:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh. What good can a woman do?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.19,1:10:43.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\pos(384.93,419)}Taihei Finance
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.73,1:10:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sawako! \NMikawa is acting like this now — {honestly no idea what's she showing, devil?}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.10,1:10:51.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs30\c&H3D2E16&\3c&HC8C39E&\fax-0.099215\fscx101.25\fscy99.68\frx-1.7997\fry-5.2678\xbord3.04\ybord2.99\org(369.2,158.51)\pos(370.71,143.56)\frz10.41}Business Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.56,1:10:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be in trouble if the higher-ups find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.56,1:10:54.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs23\pos(385.99,426.47)}Business Headquarters Manager Mikawa
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.09,1:10:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.58,1:10:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been to Goryo Trust, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.74,1:11:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I went there to promote \Nthe expeditious adoption of the Portfolio System.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.34,1:11:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And get on the couple \Nof young fund managers' nerves in doing so: {/would raise a commotion}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.58,1:11:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,"Do you put more trust \Nin computer software than in us?"
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.46,1:11:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The Portfolio System was created \Nby people vastly more experienced than them. {superior; excellent; brilliant; outstanding}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.69,1:11:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by a computer!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.62,1:11:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But you still need a permission from above...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.19,1:11:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.73,1:11:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikawa, what's the outlook on the sales promotion \Nfor that system we discussed?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.25,1:11:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sir! I dispatched Matsumoto \Nto Goryo Trust immediately
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.43,1:11:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and was in the process of receiving her report.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.73,1:11:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Report to the Department Chief!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.40,1:11:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsumoto!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.40,1:11:38.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs20\pos(389.19,429.13)}Business Headquarters Department Chief Toda {業務本部長 戸田}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.14,1:11:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The outlook is excellent. {lit: I feel the very best}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.90,1:11:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.62,1:11:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Your forecast was correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.71,1:11:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are last year's financial results \Nfor the industry leader, Iwamizu Heavy Industries. {settlement of accounts; closing accounts; financial results; reporting (of accounts)}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.42,1:12:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A slump on the maritime market \Ncaused a drop in the shipbuilding division profitability.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.38,1:12:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And the aircraft division also went off track.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.43,1:12:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's over 10 billion in the black!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.68,1:12:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By collecting their convertible bonds \Nat a low interest rate of just 1.2%,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.58,1:12:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they made profit with zaitech manipulations.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.72,1:12:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Uchida Merchant Fleet, \NTokiwa Factory Complex, Hinomoto Oil — {very unsure about all the names here, first one also seems kinda out of line as it's just "merchant ship"; for some reason only "hinomoto sekyu" was in manga}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.81,1:12:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,everything outside the main business is in the black. {due to their earnings - unsure why he adds that}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.61,1:12:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it comical? \NTheir earnings from side investments
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.59,1:12:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,are more than that from the main business \Nthey worked so hard for. {/busily; sedulously; laboriously; feverishly; fussily; worrying (about little things) working towards}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.03,1:12:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way, it's the same as if the office lady was earning many times her salary by investing in NTT stocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.08,1:12:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So you know Yukie's story already?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.62,1:12:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Individual shareholders only account for 20% of the Tokyo Stock Exchange, so we gotta appreciate their existence. {/they are very valuable}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.58,1:12:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who is making all that clamor over there? {no clue what she means, would assume "but still, it's so noisy in that place?" tho a big stretch, it really sounds a lot more like she's asking "even after they make all that noise?" impying maybe just the stock exchange in general, or maybe just yukie who tried to brag it personally}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.01,1:12:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Corporations, who are 80% of shareholders.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.91,1:12:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.87,1:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.64,1:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? Matsumoto here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.53,1:13:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What's taking him so long? \NHe was the one who proposed the meeting... {TLC}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.49,1:13:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad!
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.90,1:13:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Our study tour lasted for longer than scheduled. {study tour; guided visit; field trip}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.29,1:13:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Study tour?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.82,1:13:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A showcase of Yamagami Brokerage partners. {business region; marketing area; commercial sphere; trading area; region in which a business operates}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.25,1:13:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwamizu Heavy Industries, Tozai Gas,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.25,1:13:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as Hinomoto Steel Works — {/such firms as ...} {actually "koukan" is "steel pipe/tube" so idk what he meant by that; before they used the word "seitetsu" for this which makes it even more inscrutable}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.85,1:13:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,learning about the extent of lands owned by them \Ngave us all a useful insight.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.80,1:13:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you bought their stocks \Nwithout a second thought, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.70,1:13:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Well, yeah... {guess}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.53,1:13:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamagami Brokerage played you like a fiddle. {lit: "good at business; having a good head for business; good businessman; shrewd salesman" but I'm unsure whther she means this in honest sense like "they're a good company to invest into" or ironically, like "they're good at manipulating/had you by the nose"}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.81,1:13:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They are pros, after all. \NWell, we also know how to tell a good deal. {unsure, "we also won't make them/us suffer losses"}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.27,1:13:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a computer be able \Nto handle such a simple task, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.19,1:13:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.38,1:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When you gave the order to buy 1 million shares \Nof Hinomoto Steel Works,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.64,1:13:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but then learned that Tozai Insurance \Nbought 3 million shares,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.85,1:13:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you panicked and also bought 2 million more. {lit: added purchases to 3 mil.}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.40,1:13:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What now, eavesdropping on me? {/so you heard it/you've been told? - unsure, might as well be "what could I do, I was told/reported so"}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.16,1:14:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, the broker-dealer phoned other \NInstitutional Investors and fund managers as well. {/company}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.77,1:14:07.96,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,200)\bord1\blur1\fs0\fax-0.331209\fscx216.46\fscy206.63\frz16.4692\frx3.9194\fry-12.2446\org(473.79,291.25)\pos(481.32,269.56)\c&H7A9A9E&\3c&H1B1C23&}Yamagami Brokerage
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.78,1:14:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for your reference, {/telling/conveying}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.86,1:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Tozai Insurance and Goryo Trust
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.30,1:14:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,settled on buying 3 million shares each.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.60,1:14:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You want 3 million too?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.44,1:14:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.70,1:14:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...Which brings us to the events of today —
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.45,1:14:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hinomoto's shares becoming illiquid! {no clue what to make of it, panku can be "bursting; overflowing; being jammed (e.g. phone lines); reaching breaking point; collapse; breakdown; going bankrupt" so probably just "clogged up the buying queue/became impossible to trade" which I hope is kinda included in "illiquid" and I don't suppose buying company's shares en masse would be enough to make it go bankrupt}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.62,1:14:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting at?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.45,1:14:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Buying penny stocks isn't scary \Nif everyone does that. {Stocks with a stock price below about 100 yen are called " ultra-low stocks ". These stocks are sometimes called "boro stocks" because they include stocks whose performance and financial condition are in tatters and are at risk of bankruptcy.}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.53,1:14:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the ensuing loss isn't as bitter \Nwhen you're not bearing it alone. {lit: when you lose, everyone gets along well together}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.92,1:14:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I'll propose it to the director.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.76,1:14:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.34,1:14:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This "something... system" you're selling. {/selling/promoting}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.16,1:14:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"Portfolio System."
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.31,1:14:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. You bring it over \Nand put against us in a face-off.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.14,1:15:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If that fancy system of yours fails, \NI'll have you kneel right before me.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.77,1:15:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the system succeeds?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.68,1:15:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get a tonsure! {/become a monk}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.54,1:15:19.47,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\pos(379.6,433.4)}Manhattan Trust Tokyo Branch {マンハッタン・トラスト東京支社}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.51,1:15:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our Sawako!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.51,1:15:24.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs40\pos(387.06,409.94)}Anne Marie Taylor
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.17,1:15:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how you got the Goryo Trust \Nto order a Portfolio System from you?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.46,1:15:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Their Director Iida seems to have been inclined \Ntowards adopting it since long ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.81,1:15:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To anyone familiar with the stock market,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.58,1:15:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it would come across as obvious that the current \Nmarket trend is going to cease one day.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.93,1:15:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Much like to the hardships of war, \Nthe "New Breed" is oblivious to it. {I think she means hardships of post-war japan, the same as in the definition I gave before} {/those who don't know are ...}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.07,1:15:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the introduction of low interest rates \Nin autumn of 1985 to curb the strong yen, {lit is "the year before last, autumn - yen is high, low interest rates" but if I'm not liberal here, the cps would be disgusting}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.74,1:15:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the money that flowed into Kabutocho \Namounts to 200 trillion yen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.54,1:15:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The market capitalization of the listed stock \Nis 400 trillion yen.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.50,1:16:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo is on its way to surpass the New York's Wall Street,\Nbecoming the #1 stock market in the world, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.55,1:16:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the US,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.99,1:16:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in three years from 1984 to 1986, the market capitalization \Nof the stocks in circulation dropped by 10%.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.49,1:16:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason was, fearing an external takeover, \Nthe companies were repurchasing their own shares.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.73,1:16:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the fewer your shares are, \Nthe more each one costs.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.46,1:16:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it was the same for Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.31,1:16:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of stocks sold and bought \Nwas relatively small.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.14,1:16:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, among all the stocks in circulation, about 70 to 75%\Nwere exchanged through B2B schemes.{business-to-business; inter-business; inter-enterprise; B2B} {not sure what's mochiau here, hardly "things on hand; things in stock" because then, what's b2b here? assumed "exchanged/traded"}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.62,1:16:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The market, therefore, descended \Ninto a chronic shortage of stocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.52,1:16:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we look at the price-earnings ratio, \NJapan is roughly four times ahead of the US. {price-earnings ratio; P/E ratio; PER​}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.92,1:16:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, said NTT shares \Nare reaching a whopping coefficient of 200!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.05,1:16:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But why does such an abnormal situation \Nonly come into being in Japan?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.16,1:16:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of residue money, \Nnot being put to any use.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.19,1:16:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, my friend's uncle \Nworks as a subcontractor for Iwamizu Heavy Industries.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.15,1:16:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, when he came to pay off his debt...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.15,1:17:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.59,1:17:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no objections to you keeping this money \Nand using it as you see fit for some more time. {lit is "without telling return" - could be "please don't say you're returning it" or "we don't ask you to return it yet"; couldn't decided so threw away this talking part altogether bc both are kinda stupid}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.06,1:17:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say so, we don't need any more equipment \Nthat we could spend this money on.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.94,1:17:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Our parent company is too freaked out by the strong yen, \Nso the work is tapering off on our end.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.74,1:17:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You're letting us down... {lit is "weakened" but I've no clue what he means, TLC}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.21,1:17:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the ones letting {\i1}me{\i0} down!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.92,1:17:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody ever gave me that look \Nwhen I'd come to return his money!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.39,1:17:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The president of Yonemura Real Estate \Ncame to see you. {lit is "visible" but I think he means this}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.54,1:17:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.18,1:17:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid, finish with the formalities here.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.50,1:17:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.23,1:17:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If it isn't Yonemura, the Real Estate maven!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.86,1:17:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Need acquisition funds, same way as last year. {no clue what he's talking about, assuming "loan that I'll use to buy real estate"; also no clue what's rei no toshi, assumed "every year"}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.60,1:17:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like a loan?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.91,1:17:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, regarding the amount...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.12,1:17:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll lend you as much as you need!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.51,1:17:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't hold back when using it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.38,1:17:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.71,1:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you invest into the equipment, \Nthere won't be any job.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.05,1:18:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you want to buy a house, \Nthe plot would cost a fortune. {lit: "plot/land sharp rise (in prices); steep rise; substantial increase; soaring is out of one's reach; beyond one's grasp​"}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.84,1:18:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can deposit the money, \Nbut the interest rates are low.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.14,1:18:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All that money that has nowhere else to go \Nends up accumulating at Kabutocho.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.31,1:18:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The average investment yield \Nof the stock is 34% in the US. {unsure why she says sono} {interest; (investment) yield; profits}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.52,1:18:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only 0.5% in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.11,1:18:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Developing a Portfolio System that meets the needs \Nof the Japanese market is going to be a bumpy ride. {rough going; running into trouble; proceeding with difficulty; rough passage}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.32,1:18:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I was hoping for some advice from you... {/somehow, with anne's skill/ability}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.23,1:18:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, \Nyou appeal to our friendship again.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.66,1:18:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of it as of Japanese style of doing business.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.18,1:18:36.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.11,1:18:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When he invited me out, I thought, \N"Sure enough, that'd be awfully awkward!"
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.55,1:18:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, "Why don't we invite Sawako with us too?"
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.47,1:18:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can learn something new from you \Nwhile drinking with you!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.70,1:18:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, quit that farce, you! {to affect a stylish air; to try to look good; to show off}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.09,1:18:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you'd allow me... {/without delay [let's start]}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.77,1:19:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This new product you're promoting, \N"Portfolio System," right?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.61,1:19:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Straight to business! {TLC, very unsure but assumed kusaru - to have the audacity to; to be bastard enough to}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.27,1:19:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.44,1:19:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely enough, you know that the Japanese and the US markets operate so closely it's like they're tied together. {not sure what to make of "operating together; working together; being linked (to); being tied (to); being connected (with); interlocking"}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.55,1:19:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.78,1:19:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hence, the portfolio system takes into account\Nthe American long-term and short-term interest rates,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.00,1:19:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,commodities, oil and stock markets, etc etc, \Npredicting a whole assortment of indexes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.50,1:19:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to assist the fund managers \Nin making right investment decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.96,1:19:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Long story short, \Nis it a system for minimizing the losses?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.19,1:19:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't expect our national money game \Nto go on forever like this. {very unsure, but has to be "kokumin soude" - "the nation appearing all together" tho very close to kakuminsouseisan - "GNP" but this deosn't make a lot of sense}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.67,1:19:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't it a good thing? Everyone is getting richer.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.47,1:19:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, any game is bound to end, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.14,1:19:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. Moreover, "game" implies \Nthere would be a winner and a loser.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.58,1:19:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, the {\i1}game{\i0} loser \Nwill lose money as well, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.03,1:19:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.27,1:19:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That includes the NTT shares too?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.24,1:19:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as risk-free stock. {lit: there's no stock that never suffers loss}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.16,1:19:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Matsumoto never ceases to amaze! \NAh, here, let me pour you another...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.60,1:19:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to take my leave now.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.54,1:20:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got work to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:00.06,1:20:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even {\i1}this{\i0} late? {hope he means this by "after this?"}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.38,1:20:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, just the right time to make a call to the US.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.25,1:20:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the treat.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.51,1:20:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you've learned your share, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.65,1:20:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmpf! Just forget it and drink already!
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.91,1:20:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Martin. I hope you're having \Na very refreshing morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.94,1:20:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I just sent you the data on the New Breed Market, \Nwhich is overflowing with money.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.40,1:20:29.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\pos(376.93,442.99)\bord1\blur1\fs30}Manhattan Trust Head Office
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.36,1:20:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This data on the Japanese stock market \Nis absolutely fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.76,1:20:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, whenever I input new data into the system,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.70,1:20:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I need but to slightly adjust its current state, \Nso it takes little to no time. {TLC, I don't really understand what he means, usually I'd think "up to now, the data you provided only needed a slight alteration from previous system state, so it doesn't take me much time" but the wording is weird and anne looks disappointed next so it must be "it takes longer than usual because I can't ...." and i can't tell in what time he's talking}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.27,1:20:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you, Anne.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.96,1:20:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-uh. It's business.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.50,1:20:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Miss Sawako. You wanted to know \Nabout the interest rate reversal, right? {TLC, really no clue}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.47,1:20:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Here, at Kabutocho, \Nthey're gravely nervous about the US interest rate hikes. {... in Japan,}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.43,1:21:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So far, it's out of question for the US, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.68,1:21:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The stock prices always move inversely to the interest rates. \NThat would be so for any country.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.52,1:21:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If American interest rates spike, and the Japanese rates, \Nbeing directly linked to them, follow suit, {operating together; working together; being linked (to); being tied (to); being connected (with); interlocking}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.44,1:21:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Kabutocho would come under the biggest ever bank run, \Nand the risk a of major crash would become very real.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.85,1:21:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Kabutocho is full of anticipation for when the violently fluctuating interest rates eventually reach the breaking point
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.78,1:21:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and start climbing rapidly. {/is morbidly curious, when will ... }
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.82,1:21:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, \NI don't register any trends suggestive of a spike{ in the interest rates}.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.41,1:21:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You've nothing to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.75,1:21:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. If you notice any suspicious trend, \Nplease let me know.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.69,1:21:55.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\pos(400.92,340.64)}Yamagami Brokerage {山上証券}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.69,1:21:59.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs40\pos(407.85,413.67)}Sales Department {営業部}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.35,1:22:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Presently, the stock market is jumping at its own shadow, \Neveryone is on pins and needles. {suspicion will raise bogies; once you suspect something, everything else will look suspicious; jumping at shadows​}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.10,1:22:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be the apprehension \Nof the ghost of Rothschilds reappearing?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.13,1:22:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be exactly that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.57,1:22:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When everyone is alarmed by the high prices,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.92,1:22:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the {monetary circulation on the }international currency market \Nis shrouded in uncertainty,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.24,1:22:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody has any confidence\Nabout making one move or another.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.54,1:22:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, why won't we let out \Nthe ghosts of Rothschilds ourselves? {hope}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.48,1:22:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as I'm aware, the New Breed \Nis universally intolerant to the ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.52,1:22:33.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs40\pos(378.53,333.18)\frz359.2}Goryo Trust Bank {五菱信託銀行}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.87,1:22:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Yamagami Brokerage placed an order \Nfor selling a huge chunk of their large-cap stocks.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.91,1:22:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamagami selling so early into the month is a rare sight.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.56,1:22:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Is it true that your company is selling? {TLC, no clue what he means, but must be "it's about your recent sale"; after rewatching the whole episode I still don't quite understand the nature of relationship between yamagami and oiwa - this oiwa never mentioned again, so it could be it wasn't a bank and just city/director's name/department of yamagami}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.33,1:22:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in case American interest rates \Nsuddenly turn around and start rising,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.51,1:22:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we're converting part of our assets into cash. {actually "money on hand ratio; proportion; percentage increasing" but I've no clue what he means, could be "increasing reserves of ..."}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.09,1:22:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? You nearly spooked me there. Thanks. {/scared}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.32,1:23:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very strange move all the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.72,1:23:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling 34 million shares all at once...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.89,1:23:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, they're suspending the trade again.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.57,1:23:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on? Of 250 Ticker Symbols listed, \Ntrading is suspended for 70 already! {hope he means this by "trading name of stocks and securities"}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.74,1:23:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we witnessing the advent \Nof a historical market crash?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.41,1:23:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In just under 50 minutes, \Nthe market average is down by 1,000 yen already! {TLC, no clue what he means by "1000 yen also plummeted", could be exchange rate but why measure it in 1000s and what does it have to do with stock market? assumed the average fall in stock prices market-wide tho 1000 yen seems a bit too wild a change}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.37,1:23:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Saya, selling 300! {??? guess}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.16,1:23:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hayate, 5,000 sold! {?}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.40,1:23:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All 12 million shares of Hinomoto are sold?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.92,1:23:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.57,1:23:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Selling? Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.76,1:23:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell! Sell everything!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.74,1:23:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sell! Sure thing, everything! {/naturally}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.76,1:23:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If this continues, \Neveryone's combined losses would be immense. {lit is "crowded with"}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.97,1:23:49.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\fade(0,200)}Fund Management Department {資金運用部 大岩}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:49.23,1:23:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Matsumoto!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.61,1:23:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Director?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.56,1:23:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The Portfolio System we've discussed before \Nis completed now.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.03,1:23:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if it's complete now, it's already obsolete! {unsure what he means: being too late; losing one's final chance}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.76,1:24:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The American interest rates are about to turn around. {they say}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.37,1:24:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The market average dropped \Nby 1,000 yen in 50 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.76,1:24:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,May I use your phone?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.14,1:24:11.23,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs50\pos(378.53,403.01)\c&HE5F7FD&}New York
Dialogue: 0,1:24:12.58,1:24:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sawako?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.11,1:24:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's midnight on our end.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.96,1:24:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.07,1:24:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But the rumors of imminent reversal \Nin American interest rates are circulating like crazy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.79,1:24:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any truth to it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.09,1:24:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Disinformation. {faked information; bogus intelligence; disinformation}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.55,1:24:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing more than a false rumor from Practor Brokerage. \NIt was debunked soon after. {actually " to cancel; to withdraw; to retract; to take back (words, etc.); to revoke"; also no clue wht's this purakuta}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.73,1:24:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, before being debunked, it was leaked to Japan, \Nwhere it took on a life of its own?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.69,1:24:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. May you have \Nthe sweetest dreams tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.02,1:24:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Sawako? Give me a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.66,1:24:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? Even a 1,000 yen drop in market average \Nis nothing to be worried about.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.43,1:24:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that when the market index median was at 15,600 yen, {honestly not sure this nikkei is Nikkei (newspaper, share index)​}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.63,1:24:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the weighting was different \Nfrom that of now, at 24,500 yen. {hon, not a single clue what she's talking about, I cannot understand the weighting concept}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.40,1:24:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But everyone is too afraid of the possible growth, \Nto the point where their judgment is hazed. {not sure what to make of "high place; high ground; height; (high) altitude; elevation​"}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.84,1:25:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawako, our portfolio system says, "buy now." \NThe rationale is...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.78,1:25:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I put my trust in your system.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.60,1:25:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Start buying!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.13,1:25:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy it all!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.60,1:25:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Director!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.73,1:25:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up! I assume full responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.17,1:25:19.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\bord1\blur1\fs30\pos(400.39,343.84)}Yamagami Brokerage {山上証券 / shouken}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.17,1:25:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Buying?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.15,1:25:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not funny! {guess, iindesune?}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.74,1:25:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Goryo Trust, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.71,1:25:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the ghost of the Rothschilds \Nfinally start possessing them? {no clue what he means by "felt/noticed"}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.14,1:25:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? The decline has stopped after a downfall of 1,066 yen. {/after falling down } {actually says both "yen depreciacion" and "drop" so not sure what goes where here}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.02,1:25:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the buying orders are placed one after another!
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.16,1:25:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The first to switch to large-scale buying was... \NYamagami Brokerage?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.30,1:25:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting. But does that mean\NYamagami were just aiming to sell short?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.16,1:25:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, the market average \Nonly decreased by 182 yen 55 sen. {again, doesn't say what did so assuming}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.63,1:25:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's the best the New Breed can do? {no clue what he means: our gracious (e.g. Queen); honorific that attaches to name of a person or thing that has bestowed grace or favour upon you; TLC}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.08,1:25:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Rothschild ended with a great triumph.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.51,1:26:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you again.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.32,1:26:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.43,1:26:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The system proved reliable beyond expectations. {/accurate/exact}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.58,1:26:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was all thanks to the trust \Nthat you put in our system.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.37,1:26:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? It's just that I distrust the New Breed, \Nwho are oblivious to the caution, even more. {hope, TLc}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.43,1:26:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you know \Nif we don't belong to New Breed as well?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.90,1:26:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can be pretty sure \Nwe're not the "Old Guard." {TLC, no cluye what's before jinrui but wispers hears it "旧" so I'm believing, but still no clue what she means, could be "I'm not ..." could be "aren't you"}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.58,1:26:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you made someone from the New Breed \Nreflect on his ways for sure. {regret; repentance; remorse; being sorry}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.40,1:26:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. 1,000 shares. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.40,1:26:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you, Rothschild.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.81,1:26:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The ghost of the Rothschilds \Nwas nothing more than an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.53,1:26:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it would still be premature \Nto pronounce the ghost dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.49,1:26:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Dormant again, the ghost is waiting patiently \Nfor its next chance to strike. {/While holding its breath ... turn at the stage}
